  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000140">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula plug</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">plug valve</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A high pressure valve with a rotatable plug that allows or denies flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PLUG VALVE&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY VALVE&gt; that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A rotary valve that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary valve that has a quarter turn action in which the closure member is a cylindrical or tapered plug which operates by rotating on its axis and sealing against a downstream seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A quarter-turn valve whose closure element is usually a tapered plug having a rectangular port.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2458"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2459"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification requires necessary conditions only. Under OWA, any artifact with a plug closure and quarter-turn mechanism would be forcibly classified as a plug valve, but specialized multi-port valves or custom manifolds containing plug mechanisms should not automatically inherit the standard plug valve classification without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PlugValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃p(PlugClosure(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃r(QuarterTurnRotationProcess(r) ∧ participatesIn(x,r)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every plug valve is a valve that has a plug closure component and participates in quarter-turn rotation processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula plug é uma válvula que possui um elemento de fechamento em forma de plugue cilíndrico ou cônico que opera por rotação de um quarto de volta em seu eixo para controlar o fluxo de fluido selando contra um assento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A plug valve is a valve that has a cylindrical or tapered plug closure member which operates by quarter-turn rotation on its axis to control fluid flow by sealing against a seat.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VaporOutlet">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">saída de vapor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vapor outlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Outlet"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000303">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">incinerator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">incinerador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every incinerator is a furnace that bears a waste combustion function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An incinerator is a furnace that is designed to combust waste material for disposal purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um incinerador é um forno que é projetado para combustir material de resíduo para fins de descarte.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INCINERATOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FURNACE&gt; that is intended for the combustion of waste material</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A furnace that is intended for the combustion of waste material.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Also known as an enclosed combustor                  Flares are not 100% efficient, and some methane (un-combusted) is emitted during flaring as a result of un-combusted gas being released via the equipment exhaust stream. Flares cannot be performance tested to guarantee that they achieve the same efficiency as an incinerator or enclosed combustor. Studies suggest that the efficiency of a flare during windy conditions can be as low as 50%. The many components and complex network of small gathering lines in flare are a source of fugitive emissions.                  Incinerators are used when flaring is not a viable option. The combustion efficiency of an incinerator is known to be over 99% which is higher than a flare. Plus, they are more suitable for applications involving carcinogenic gases like BTEX and H2S applications. Incineration of waste gas products may not be a new concept for the                  oil and gas industry however, in recent years the design and technology have resulted in optimal performance, increased reliability and reduce capital and operating costs for operators.                  An enclosed combustor is a newer iteration of the incinerator. The combustion device is completely enclosed except for the combustion air intake and the exhaust discharge. It operates like an incinerator with more restriction to allow it to be able to operate in a reduced spacing capacity. The surfaces exposed to the atmosphere operate below the temperature that would ignite a flammable substance present in the surrounding area. Because of the reduced space capacity all air intakes must be equipped with a flame arresting device as a safety feature to allow the unit to be 10 meters away from wells or operating equipment. https://energynow.com/2021/07/the-differences-between-flares-incinerators-and-enclosed-combustors/</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1942"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Incinerator(x) ↔ Furnace(x) ∧ ∃f(WasteCombustionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3383">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3386"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000346">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2872"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2873"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2874"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2871"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical structure. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for shaft identity could lead to false positives - any assembly with a shaft key and rotational motion might be classified as a shaft rather than a more specific equipment type that contains a shaft. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to validate sufficiency.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que possui partes componentes incluindo chavetas de eixo para transmissão de torque e vedações de eixo para prevenção de vazamento, servindo como o elemento rotativo central em máquinas rotativas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that has component parts including shaft keys for torque transmission and shaft seals for leakage prevention, serving as the core rotating element in rotating machinery.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shaft is an assembly that transmits power through rotation and has shaft keys, shaft seals, and shaft sleeves as essential components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Shaft(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃k(ShaftKey(k) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,k)) ∧ ∃s(ShaftSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(ShaftSleeve(l) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ENGINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the core rotating element on which the rotating parts are mounted and through which energy is either transmitted from the prime mover or generated in case of a driver.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] a positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A positive displacement pump which contains a displacing element intended to be moved in a reciprocating movement to exert pressure on a fluid, typically moving within a cylindrical space.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of fluid pump in which reciprocating pistons or plungers displace the fluid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A piston pump.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba alternativa</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reciprocating pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2673"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2674"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2672"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2675"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2676"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2677"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A reciprocating pump is a pump that contains pistons or plungers designed to move in a reciprocating motion within cylindrical chambers to displace fluid through positive displacement action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba alternativa é uma bomba que contém pistões ou êmbolos projetados para se moverem em movimento alternativo dentro de câmaras cilíndricas para deslocar fluido através de ação de deslocamento positivo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ReciprocatingPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃m(ReciprocatingDisplacementMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃p(PistonOrPlunger(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃c(CylindricalChamber(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every reciprocating pump is a pump that has as component part at all times a reciprocating displacement mechanism and has as component part at all times pistons or plungers and has as component part at all times cylindrical chambers.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under Open World Assumption, asserting equivalence based on structural differentia could lead to false positives where complex equipment containing reciprocating elements (like reciprocating compressors with auxiliary pumps, or hybrid systems) might be incorrectly classified as standard reciprocating pumps. The structural mechanism is necessary but sufficient conditions require domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1805">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000068"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ProtectedTemperatureSensingElement">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">protected temperature sensing element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento protegido de temperatura de sensoriamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000212">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The positively charged site in a cell. Oxidation site. The site of metal loss in corrosion.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The half of a battery that is positively charged and to which anions migrate by electrostatic attraction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from the medium of lower conductivity.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ANODE&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL DEVICE&gt; that has a capability of &lt;EMITTING&gt; positive charge carriers to, and/or &lt;RECEIVING&gt; negative charge carriers from, the medium of lower conductivity</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b120"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every anode is electrical equipment that has the function of electrochemical oxidation and has electrical connection and active material as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Anode(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(AnodeFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ânodo é um equipamento elétrico que possui a função de servir como eletrodo positivo em processos eletroquímicos, capaz de emitir portadores de carga positiva para e/ou receber portadores de carga negativa de um meio de menor condutividade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An anode is electrical equipment that bears the function of serving as the positive electrode in electrochemical processes, capable of emitting positive charge carriers to and/or receiving negative charge carriers from a medium of lower conductivity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">ânodo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">anode</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2733">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidConductionFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Tower">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tower</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">torre</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2550">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000341">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTARY PUMP&gt; is a &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A positive displacement pump that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A positive displacement pump that consists of a chamber containing gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (RotaryPump(x) → PositiveDisplacementPump(x) ∧ ∃y (RotaryDisplacementMechanism(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ¬∃z (SeparateInletValve(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ¬∃w (SeparateOutletValve(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2747"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000331"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2746"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2745"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2748"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba rotativa</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotary pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba rotativa é uma bomba de deslocamento positivo que contém uma câmara com engrenagens, cames, parafusos, palhetas, êmbolos ou elementos similares acionados pela rotação relativa do eixo de acionamento ou carcaça, e que não possui válvulas separadas de entrada e saída.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A rotary pump is a positive displacement pump that contains a chamber with gears, cams, screws, vanes, plungers or similar elements actuated by relative rotation of the drive shaft or casing, and which has no separate inlet and outlet valves.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every rotary pump is a positive displacement pump that has a rotary displacement mechanism as component part and lacks separate inlet and outlet valves.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While the rotary mechanism is clearly necessary for rotary pumps, making it sufficient under OWA could lead to false positives where complex equipment containing rotary elements (like gearboxes with pumping side-effects or hybrid machines) might be misclassified as standard rotary pumps. The constructive differentia should be validated by domain experts before upgrading to equivalence.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000318">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PigLauncher(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(PigLaunchingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(PipelineConnection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure vessel intended for sending a pig into a pipeline.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIG LAUNCHER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;LAUNCHING&gt; a &lt;PIPE PIG&gt; into a pipeline</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A chamber connected to a pipeline intended for sending pigs into the pipeline.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pig launcher is a vessel that bears a pig launching function for inserting pipeline pigs into pipeline systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um lançador de pig é um vaso que possui função de lançamento de pig para inserir pigs de duto em sistemas de tubulação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">lançador de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig launcher</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2314"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pig launcher is a vessel that has the function to launch pipeline pigs and has a pipeline connection component.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000223">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sistema de proteção catódica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cathodic protection system</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cathodic protection system is a corrosion protection system that bears a cathodic protection function and has anodes as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um sistema de proteção catódica é um sistema de proteção contra corrosão que usa mecanismos eletroquímicos de proteção catódica com ânodos para prevenir a corrosão de equipamentos ou estruturas de aço carbono e baixa liga.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cathodic protection system is a corrosion protection system that uses electrochemical cathodic protection mechanisms with anodes to prevent corrosion of carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A corrosion protection system using sacrificial anodes or impressed current anodes offering material and giving protection to carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CATHODIC PROTECTION SYSTEM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;CORROSION PROTECTION SYSTEM&gt; using sacrificial anodes or impressed current anodes offering material and giving protection to carbon and low-alloy steel equipment or structures</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b406"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CathodicProtectionSystem(x) ↔ CorrosionProtectionSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(CathodicProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃a(Anode(a) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,a)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000251">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de pressão que porta uma função de medição de pressão diferencial e que consiste em detectar a diferença de pressão entre duas mídias fluidas ou pontos de conexão para permitir a medição de pressão diferencial através de deflexão mecânica proporcional à diferença de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pressure element that bears a differential pressure measurement function and that consists in sensing the pressure difference between two fluid media or connection points to enable measurement of differential pressure through mechanical deflection proportional to the pressure difference.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement equivalentTo PressureElement and bearerOf some DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b989"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento medidor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure measuring element</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(x) ↔ (PressureElement(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; for the measurement of &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000215">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mancal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bearing</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object intended to support and locate a moving or static element and capable of reducing friction and transfer forces in a connection.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BEARING&gt; is a &lt;SUPPORT&gt; intended to support and locate a moving or static element</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every bearing is a material artifact that bears a support function and participates in friction reduction processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b211"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Bearing(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(FrictionReductionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A bearing is a material artifact that is designed to support and locate moving or static mechanical elements while reducing friction in the connection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um mancal é um artefato material que é projetado para suportar e localizar elementos mecânicos móveis ou estáticos enquanto reduz o atrito na conexão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidTransportFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1563"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2425"/>
