  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000291">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">globe valve body</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de válvula globo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A valve body that has a globular geometry designed to accommodate the perpendicular flow path and disc closure mechanism characteristic of globe valve operation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um corpo de válvula que possui geometria globular projetada para acomodar o caminho de fluxo perpendicular e o mecanismo de fechamento por disco característico da operação de válvula globo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1755"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000078"/>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GLOBE VALVE BODY&gt; is a &lt;VALVE BODY&gt; of a globe valve</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GlobeValveBody(x) → ValveBody(x) ∧ ∃g (GlobularGeometry(g) ∧ hasDesignCharacteristic(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural geometry. Under OWA, asserting equivalence based on globular geometry alone could lead to false classifications of complex assemblies or hybrid components that contain globular elements but should not be classified as standard globe valve bodies.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every globe valve body is a valve body that has globular geometry for perpendicular flow path accommodation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000101">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000073"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b418"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b419"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifugal compressor is a compressor that uses one or more centrifugal impellers to accelerate gas through radial flow and generate pressure increase by centrifugal action.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um compressor centrífugo é um compressor que usa um ou mais impelidores centrífugos para acelerar o gás através de fluxo radial e gerar aumento de pressão por ação centrífuga.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type because under OWA, any equipment with a centrifugal impeller could be incorrectly classified as a standard centrifugal compressor, including specialized hybrid equipment or multi-stage systems that contain centrifugal elements but should not be forced into this maintenance category. Domain expert validation needed to confirm structural differentia is sufficient.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000101"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL COMPRESSOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;COMPRESSOR&gt; in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial, and generates pressure increase by means of centrifugal action and a volute or diffuser casing.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A dynamic compressor in which one ore more impellers accelerate the gas and where the main flow through the impeller is radial.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CentrifugalCompressor(x) → Compressor(x) ∧ ∃i(CentrifugalImpeller(i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i)) ∧ ∃p(RadialFlowPattern(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal compressor is a compressor that has component part at all times some centrifugal impeller and participates in some radial flow pattern.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">compressor centrífugo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal compressor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">choke valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula choke</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function and has a flow restriction element as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHOKE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; in which a solid cylinder is raised and lowered, and which is placed around or inside another cylinder that has holes or slots. The design of a choke valve means fluids flowing through the cage are coming from all sides and that the streams of flow (through the holes or slots) collide with each other at the center of the cage cylinder, thereby dissipating the energy of the fluid through flow impingement. The main advantage of choke valves is that they can be designed to be totally linear in their flow rate</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that can be used to obstruct the fluid passing inside, and has the ability to reduce the pressure from the inlet port to the outlet port.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b490"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000105"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A choke valve is a valve that bears a pressure reduction function, designed to reduce fluid pressure from inlet to outlet through controlled flow restriction and energy dissipation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula choke é uma válvula que possui uma função de redução de pressão, projetada para reduzir a pressão do fluido da entrada para a saída através de restrição controlada do fluxo e dissipação de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChokeValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
