  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000104">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle de choke é uma válvula de controle que possui um componente de geometria de choke para redução de pressão através de restrição de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A choke control valve is a control valve that has a choke geometry component for pressure reduction through flow restriction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle de choke</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">choke control valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b475"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b476"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChokeControlValve(x) → ControlValve(x) ∧ ∃y (ChokeGeometry(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every choke control valve is a control valve that has a choke geometry component at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHOKE CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; and a &lt;CHOKE VALVE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A choke valve that is equipped with an actuator that manipulates a stream of fluid in the response to a signal from an external sensing element and with input of energy from an external source.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is classified as 'both' functional and constructive. The constructive differentia (choke geometry) makes it safer to use necessary conditions to avoid forcing all valves with choke components into this specific control category under the Open World Assumption.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2955">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2951"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000216">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bell nipple</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">bell nipple</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BELL NIPPLE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a large diameter &lt;PIPING NETWORK SEGMENT&gt; fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A Bell nipple is a section of large diameter pipe fitted to the top of the blowout preventers that the flow line attaches to via a side outlet, to allow the drilling fluid to flow back over the shale shakers to the mud tanks. Also an enlarged pipe at the top of a casing string that serves as a funnel to guide drilling tools into the top of a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A funnel shaped pipe at the top of the casing that guides tool string entry and may have a side port for fluid pumping.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um bell nipple é um tubo que conduz fluidos de perfuração em operações de perfuração e é caracterizado por um diâmetro alargado que serve como funil e uma localização no conjunto da cabeça do poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A bell nipple is a pipe that conducts drilling fluids in drilling operations and is characterized by an enlarged diameter that serves as a funnel and a location at the wellhead assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(BellNipple(x) ↔ (Pipe(x) ∧ ∃f(DrillingFluidConductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(EnlargedDiameter(s) ∧ hasCharacteristicShape(x,s)) ∧ ∃l(WellheadAssembly(l) ∧ hasLocation(x,l))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000216"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b235"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every bell nipple is a pipe that bears a DrillingFluidConductionFunction and has an enlarged diameter shape and is located at a wellhead assembly.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2279">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000174"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3216">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SupportMechanism"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Absorber">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A functional object that absorbs.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A vertical, cylindrical vessel that recovers heavier (longer carbon chain) hydrocarbons from a mixture of lighter hydrocarbons.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ABSORBER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;ABSORBING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">absorber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">absorvedor</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b14"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every absorber is a separator that has the function to absorb specific components from fluid mixtures through mass transfer to an absorbent phase</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Absorber(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(AbsorptionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um absorvedor é um vaso de pressão que realiza uma função de absorção para transferência seletiva de massa de componentes de uma mistura fluida para uma fase absorvente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An absorber is a pressure vessel that realizes an absorption function for selective mass transfer of components from a fluid mixture into an absorbent phase.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000282">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1591"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um fusível é um equipamento elétrico que protege circuitos interrompendo o fluxo de corrente através do derretimento intencional de um elemento fusível quando a corrente excede valores especificados por uma duração suficiente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fuse is an electrical equipment that protects circuits by interrupting current flow through the intentional melting of a fusible element when current exceeds specified values for a sufficient duration.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fusível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fuse</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that by the fusing of one or more of its specially designed and proportioned components, opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FUSE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PROTECTOR&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRICAL ELEMENT&gt; that opens the circuit in which it is inserted by breaking the current when this exceeds a given value for a sufficient time</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fuse is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and has a fuse element that melts under overcurrent conditions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Fuse(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FuseElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000357">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A switchgear and controlgear bearing a set of switches for connecting and disconnecting the various circuits of an electrical system, as of a telegraph, telephone, etc.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A switchgear and controlgear bearing a set of switches for connecting and disconnecting the various circuits of an electrical system, as of a telegraph, telephone, etc.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SWITCHBOARD&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SWITCHING DEVICE&gt;that is one or more panels accommodating control switches, indicators, and other apparatus for operating electric circuits</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Switchboard(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃p,s,i(Panel(p) ∧ ElectricalSwitch(s) ∧ ControlIndicator(i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i)) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalCircuitControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every switchboard is electrical equipment that has component parts (panels, switches, indicators) and bears the function to control electrical circuits</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">quadro de distribuição</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">switchboard</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um quadro de distribuição é um equipamento elétrico que consiste em painéis que acomodam chaves, indicadores e aparatos de controle para conectar, desconectar e controlar vários circuitos de um sistema elétrico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A switchboard is electrical equipment that consists of panels accommodating switches, indicators, and control apparatus for connecting, disconnecting, and controlling various circuits of an electrical system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3052"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que participa em movimento rotacional e tem um eixo do rotor como componente essencial, projetado para transferir energia mecânica através de movimento rotacional dentro de um conjunto de máquina.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that participates in rotational motion and has a rotor shaft as an essential component, designed to transfer mechanical energy through rotational motion within a machine assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">rotor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Rotor(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃p(RotationalMotionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(RotorShaft(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every Rotor is an Assembly that participates in some RotationalMotionProcess and has some rotor shaft as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2756"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration (rotating portion with shaft), providing sufficient conditions under OWA could lead to overclassification. Complex assemblies containing rotating elements might be incorrectly classified as rotors rather than their proper categories (motors, compressors, etc.).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;ROTOR&gt; is a &lt;MACHINE COMPONENT&gt; that is the rotating portion of a machine</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The rotating shaft in a PDM motor.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b584">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b588"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000286">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1645"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GasTurbine(x) ↔ Turbine(x) ∧ ∃c,h(Compressor(c) ∧ CombustionChamber(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h)) ∧ ∃p1,p2(AirCompressionProcess(p1) ∧ FuelCombustionProcess(p2) ∧ participatesIn(x,p1) ∧ participatesIn(x,p2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A turbine that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GAS TURBINE&gt; is a &lt;TURBINE&gt; that compresses air which is then mixed with fuel for combustion and expansion through a turbine section to generate relatively high power output for either mechanical drive or power generation</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">turbina a gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas turbine</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas turbine is a turbine that has an integrated compressor and combustion chamber, designed to compress ambient air, mix it with fuel for combustion, and expand the resulting hot gases through a turbine section to generate mechanical power.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma turbina a gás é uma turbina que possui um compressor e câmara de combustão integrados, projetada para comprimir ar ambiente, misturá-lo com combustível para combustão, e expandir os gases quentes resultantes através de uma seção de turbina para gerar energia mecânica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas turbine is a turbine that has component parts compressor and combustion chamber at all times, and participates in air compression process and fuel combustion process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The set of valves, spools, and fittings connected to the top of a well to direct and control the flow of formation fluids from the well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHRISTMAS TREE&gt; is a &lt;PIPING SYSTEM&gt; that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The control sections that sits above the basic wellhead. It may contain hangers, master valves, annular valves, wing valves, and gauges or pressure, flow rate or monitoring measurement equipment.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is an assembly of pipes and piping parts, with valves and associated control equipment that is connected to the top of a wellhead and is intended for control of fluid from a well.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A christmas tree is an assembly that bears a well fluid control function, is connected to a wellhead, and contains master valves for controlling formation fluids from oil and gas wells.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma árvore de natal é um conjunto que possui uma função de controle de fluidos de poço, está conectada a uma cabeça de poço, e contém válvulas mestras para controlar fluidos de formação de poços de petróleo e gás.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ChristmasTree(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(WellFluidControlFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellhead(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)) ∧ ∃v(MasterValve(v) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,v))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b498"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every christmas tree is an assembly that has the function to control well fluids and is connected to a wellhead and has master valves as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000228"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">árvore de natal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">christmas tree</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1752">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2638">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2640"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2087">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000172"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FeedInlet">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">feed inlet</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">entrada de alimentação</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3388">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3385"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000241">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any device that helps remove gas from circulated fluid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device that removes air or gases (methane, H2S, CO2, and others) from drilling liquids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DEGASSER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a  &lt;FLASH SEPARATOR&gt; that is a device used in drilling to remove gasses from drilling fluid which could otherwise form bubbles</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A device that removes air or gases (methane, H2S, CO2 and others) from drilling liquids.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um degaseificador é um separador que remove gases de fluidos de perfuração realizando uma função de degaseificação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A degasser is a separator that removes gases from drilling fluids by realizing a degassing function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b784"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">degasser</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">degaseificador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Degasser(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f (DegassingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every degasser is a separator that bears a degassing function and has drilling fluid as input and degassed drilling fluid plus separated gases as outputs.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000269">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While finned tubes are the defining structural feature, making sufficient conditions (equivalence) under Open World Assumption could lead to false positives where any assembly containing finned tubes would be classified as this specific heat exchanger type, including complex multi-function equipment or specialized hybrid systems.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1322"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1321"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1320"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1323"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor de tubos aletados</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">finned tube heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FinnedTubeHeatExchanger(x) → HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃y(FinnedTube(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A heat exchanger that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FINNED TUBE HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is an &lt;INDIRECT CONTACT HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; that has finned tubes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A heat exchange that has finned tubes.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A finned tube heat exchanger is a heat exchanger that has finned tubes as the primary heat transfer surface enhancement mechanism.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor de tubos aletados é um trocador de calor que possui tubos aletados como mecanismo primário de aumento da superfície de transferência de calor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000304">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1980"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de injeção é uma bomba especificamente projetada para injetar fluido em reservatórios ou sistemas de produção, tipicamente em pressões relativamente altas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An injection pump is a pump that is specifically designed to inject fluid into reservoirs or production systems, typically at relatively high pressures.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every injection pump is a pump that bears an injection function for delivering fluids to reservoirs or production systems.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Any pump used to inject fluid into the reservoir or production system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INJECTION PUMP&gt; is a &lt; POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; that is typically applied for relatively high pressures in case of injection systems</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(InjectionPump(x) ↔ Pump(x) ∧ ∃f(InjectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ForceTransmissionFunction">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3345"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3344"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transmissão de força</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">force transmission function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a ForceTransmissionProcess and that consists in transmitting mechanical force or motion from one component to another through direct physical coupling.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3238">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TubingHangerSupportStructure"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2560">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureSensingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing or casing provides containment and protection for internal components, maintaining separation between the internal mechanism and external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural body provides containment and directional guidance for fluid flow while housing internal valve components that control the flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a casing provides protective containment around internal components, maintaining their operational environment and structural integrity while allowing controlled access for maintenance.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural housing provides containment and protection for mechanical components, creating a defined boundary between internal mechanisms and the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a casing provides protective containment around mechanical components while enabling controlled fluid passage through designed openings and maintaining pressure boundaries.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing structure provides physical containment and environmental protection for internal components, shielding them from external conditions such as moisture, dust, mechanical impact, and temperature variations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a housing artifact creates and maintains a protective boundary around internal components, simultaneously providing structural support and environmental separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a body or housing artifact provides structural containment and protection for internal mechanical components or assemblies.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">enclosure process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de proteção e invólucro</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b580">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MovementCompensationProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1149">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HousingEnclosure"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000227">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b470"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ClosureMember"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000370"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural role and mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions would force classification of any artifact with backflow prevention function and check valve association, potentially including hybrid or specialized designs that should not be automatically classified as standard closure members without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">membro de fechamento de válvula de retenção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve closure member</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValveClosureMember(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(CheckValve(y) ∧ isComponentPartOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(BackflowPreventionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é uma parte componente de uma válvula de retenção e que possui uma BackflowPreventionFunction, consistindo em um elemento mecânico que previne o refluxo de fluido bloqueando fisicamente o caminho de fluxo quando as condições de pressão indicam potencial refluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is a component part of a check valve and that bears a BackflowPreventionFunction, consisting in a mechanical element that prevents fluid flow reversal by physically blocking the flow path when pressure conditions indicate potential backflow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every check valve closure member is a MaterialArtifact that is component part of some check valve and bears some BackflowPreventionFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; that is intended to prevent back flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidConductingBore">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fluid conducting bore</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">furo de fluido de condutor</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000115">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fan is an assembly that bears a gas movement function for delivering or exhausting volumes of vapor or gas at low differential pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um ventilador é um conjunto que possui uma função de movimentação de gás para fornecer ou exaurir volumes de vapor ou gás com baixa pressão diferencial.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An 'artefact' and a 'gas pressure increase device' that is intended to deliver or exhaust volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to deliver or exhaust volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FAN&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;DELIVERING&gt; or &lt;EXHAUSTING&gt; volumes of vapour or gas at low differential pressure</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fan</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">ventilador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fan is an assembly that bears a gas movement function, and every assembly that bears a gas movement function is a fan.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Fan(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(GasMovementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1251"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2555">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b709">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b715"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2544">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1042">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InformationDisplayFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000106">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every circuit-breaker is an electrical equipment that has the function to protect circuits and participates in the process of interrupting electrical current at regular intervals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every circuit breaker is an electrical switching device that has the function to interrupt electrical current and participates in regular current interruption processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disjuntor é um equipamento elétrico que possui uma função de proteção de circuito e participa em processos de interrupção de corrente em intervalos regulares.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A circuit-breaker is an electrical equipment that bears a circuit protection function and participates in current interruption processes at regular intervals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A circuit breaker is a material artifact that bears an electrical current interruption function and regularly participates in processes that safely interrupt electrical current.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um disjuntor é um dispositivo de chaveamento elétrico que possui uma função de interrupção de corrente elétrica e participa regularmente em processos que interrompem com segurança a corrente elétrica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CIRCUIT BREAKER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRICAL APPARATUS&gt; and a &lt;SWITCHING DEVICE&gt; that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A mechanical switching device that at regular intervals interrupts an electric current.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">circuit breaker</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">disjuntor</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (CircuitBreaker(x) ↔ ElectricalSwitchingDevice(x) ∧ ∃f (ElectricalCurrentInterruptionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p (RegularInterruptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CircuitBreaker(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(CircuitProtectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(CurrentInterruptionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b552"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b544"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000106"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2069">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2071"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000154">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A temperature indicator is an indicator that measures temperature and displays the measured value locally at the instrument location.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um indicador de temperatura é um indicador que mede temperatura e exibe o valor medido localmente na localização do instrumento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every temperature indicator is an instrument that has the function of temperature indication and has component parts including a temperature sensing element and a local display.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3089"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature indicator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">indicador de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] A temperature indicator (TI) is an instrument that measures temperature and displays the measured value locally at the instrument location. It typically consists of a temperature sensing element (thermocouple, RTD, or bimetal), a transmitting or mechanical linkage, and a local display. Unlike a temperature transmitter, it does not produce a standardized remote output signal; its function is limited to local indication for operator reading.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (TemperatureIndicator(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (TemperatureIndicationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s (TemperatureSensingElement(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃d (LocalDisplay(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2111">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LevelMeasurementAndTransmissionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CompressionIgnitionSystem">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compression ignition system</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sistema de compressão de ignição</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1396">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlareStack"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1450">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FeedInlet"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b711">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Tower"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000293">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HEADER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PIPING NETWORK SEGMENT&gt; that is pipe or manifold that is used to collect the discharge from many smaller pipes (a collecting header) , or can be used to distribute fluid to many smaller pipes (distributing header)</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The location, acquisition and processing parameters, and other pertinent information attached to a well log, seismic record and traces.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1780"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">header</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">header</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Header ≡ manifold ⊓ ∃connects_to.SmallPipe ⊓ ∃participatesIn.MultiStreamDistributionProcess</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A header is a manifold that connects to many smaller pipes for collecting discharge from multiple sources or distributing fluid to multiple destinations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um header é um manifold que se conecta a muitos tubos menores para coletar descarga de múltiplas fontes ou distribuir fluido para múltiplos destinos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Header(x) ↔ (manifold(x) ∧ ∃y(SmallPipe(y) ∧ connects_to(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(MultiStreamDistributionProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000273">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1379"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1377"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1378"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLANGE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar, or rib for strength or for attachment to another object</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is a projecting flat rim, plate, collar or rib.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A common, high pressure wellhead connection, using bolt attached flange plates and metal-to-metal seals.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A connection profile used in pipe work and associated equipment to provide a means of assembling and disassembling components.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um flange é um artefato material caracterizado por uma geometria de aro plano projetante, placa, colar ou nervura, projetado para fornecer conexão mecânica entre componentes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flange is a material artifact characterized by a projecting flat rim, plate, collar, or rib geometry, designed to provide mechanical connection between components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flange</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">flange</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by structural geometry. Under OWA, any artifact with projecting flat rim geometry would be forced into the flange category, which could incorrectly classify specialized equipment or complex assemblies that contain flange-like features but serve different primary functions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Flange(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃g(ProjectingFlatRimGeometry(g) ∧ hasCharacteristic(x,g)) ∧ ∃f(MechanicalConnectionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flange is a material artifact that has a projecting flat rim geometry and has the function of mechanically connecting components.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b114">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000026"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which electrical power at one voltage and current level is converted to electrical power at a different voltage and current level through electromagnetic induction in a transformer winding system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which electrical energy is converted from one voltage level to another by a transformer through electromagnetic induction between primary and secondary windings, resulting in power transfer at the desired voltage level.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de transformação de energia elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical power transformation process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SupportingProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de suporte</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">supporting process</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2518">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000363"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000149">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2845"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2846"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">self operating valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula auto-operante</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that includes a means of operation (e.g. spring / gravity / fluid pressure / counter balance), and is not depending on an external source of energy.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SELF-OPERATING VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION FUNCTION&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; that includes a means of operation (e.g. spring / gravity / fluid pressure / counter balance), and is not depending on an external source of energy</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every self-operating valve is a valve that has a self-operating mechanism as component part at all times and bears the capability of energy-independent operation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical configuration (self-operating mechanism). Under OWA, any valve with an internal operating mechanism might be classified as self-operating even if it has additional external actuators or specialized applications. Domain expert validation needed to confirm structural differentia is sufficient.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula auto-operante é uma válvula que inclui um mecanismo interno de operação (como mola, gravidade, pressão do fluido ou contrapeso) e não depende de uma fonte externa de energia para seu acionamento.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A self-operating valve is a valve that includes an internal means of operation (such as spring, gravity, fluid pressure, or counterbalance) and does not depend on an external source of energy for its actuation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SelfOperatingValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃m(SelfOperatingMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃c(EnergyIndependentOperationCapability(c) ∧ bearerOf(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureSignalPair">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">par de pressão de sinal</rdfs:label>
