  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b829">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b830"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000362">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact that accepts information in the form of a physical or chemical variable (its input variable) and converts it into an output variable of the same or another nature, according to a definite law.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSDUCER&gt; is an &lt;ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is capable of converting a &lt;PROCESS VARIABLE&gt; in one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude of the same energy</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a general term for a device, which can be a primary element, transmitter, relay, converter or other device, that receives information in the form of one or more physical quantities, modifies the information or its form, or both if required, and produces a resultant output signal.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3165"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transducer is an instrument that bears a TransductionFunction to convert information from one form or magnitude of energy to another form or magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transdutor é um instrumento que possui uma FunçãoDeTransdução para converter informação de uma forma ou magnitude de energia para outra forma ou magnitude.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transducer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transdutor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Transducer(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f (TransductionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transducer is an instrument that has the designed function to convert energy or signal forms while preserving information content.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2171">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidDistributionProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000363">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3208"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transmitter housing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">invólucro de transmissor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure as housing. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for transmitter housing would require specifying exact structural features (materials, dimensions, sealing mechanisms) that distinguish it from other instrument housings. The necessary conditions establish the core identity without risking false positives from other housing types that might share some structural features.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro de transmissor é uma Assembly que possui uma EnclosureFunction e que tem um circuito eletrônico de transmissor como parte componente em todos os momentos, projetado para fornecer proteção ambiental e contenção física para componentes do transmissor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transmitter housing is an Assembly that bears an EnclosureFunction and that has a transmitter electronic circuit as a component part at all times, designed to provide environmental protection and physical containment for transmitter components.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">TransmitterHousing ⊑ Assembly ⊓ ∃bearerOf.EnclosureFunction ⊓ ∃hasComponentPartAtAllTimes.TransmitterElectronicCircuit</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TransmitterHousing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnclosureFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(TransmitterElectronicCircuit(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSMITTER HOUSING&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENT HOUSING&gt; of a transmitter.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000221">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b382"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact and electrical cable conduit consisting of a continuous base, raised edges and no covering</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A unit or assembly of units or sections and associated fittings forming a rigid structural system used to securely fasten or support cables and raceways.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CableTray(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(CableSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃b(ContinuousBase(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)) ∧ ∃e(RaisedEdge(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cable tray is an assembly that has the function to support cables and has a continuous base part and raised edge parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cable tray</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bandeja de cabos</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bandeja de cabos é um conjunto que possui função de suporte de cabos e consiste em uma base contínua com bordas elevadas, formando um sistema estrutural rígido para suportar e rotear cabos elétricos de forma segura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cable tray is an assembly that bears a cable support function and consists of a continuous base with raised edges, forming a rigid structural system for securely supporting and routing electrical cables.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowControlProcess">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which the flow of fluid through a conduit is regulated, directed, or interrupted by mechanical means, typically involving the movement of closure elements against seating surfaces to modify flow passages.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which fluid flow is regulated, directed, or restricted through a valve body by positioning internal closure elements to achieve desired flow characteristics.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which fluid flow is permitted, obstructed, diverted or regulated through the mechanical positioning of a closure member within the flow stream, resulting in the desired flow characteristics.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow control process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de controle de fluxo</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b779">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DegassingProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000254">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Display is an Instrument that necessarily bears an InformationDisplayFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">display</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">display</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that is intended for presenting information.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DISPLAY&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;DISPLAYING&gt; something</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Display é um Instrumento que possui uma InformationDisplayFunction e que apresenta informações visualmente para operadores ou usuários.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A Display is an Instrument that bears an InformationDisplayFunction and that presents information visually to operators or users.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1041"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Display(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(InformationDisplayFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MaterialComponent">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">componente de material</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">material component</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b636">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000157"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b637"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SampleChamber">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sample chamber</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">câmara de amostra</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PowerConditioningCircuit">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">power conditioning circuit</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">circuito de potência de condicionamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000331">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under OWA, sufficient conditions based on displacement mechanism alone could lead to false positives where specialized equipment containing displacement elements might be incorrectly classified as standard positive displacement pumps.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PositiveDisplacementPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃y(DisplacementMechanism(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(PositiveDisplacementProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2540"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2541"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2542"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every positive displacement pump is a pump that has a displacement mechanism as component part at all times and participates in positive displacement processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POSITIVE DISPLACEMENT PUMP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PUMP&gt; intended to transport liquid through the reciprocating or rotary displacement principle and with either fixed or adjustable volume flow rates. NOTE - Combine with either BARE PUMP or PUMP SYSTEM,</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of fluid pump in which the displacement volume of the pump is fixed for each rotation of the pump.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A positive displacement pump is a pump that transports liquid through reciprocating or rotary displacement principle with fixed displacement volume per cycle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de deslocamento positivo é uma bomba que transporta líquido através do princípio de deslocamento alternativo ou rotativo com volume de deslocamento fixo por ciclo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de deslocamento positivo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">positive displacement pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalForce">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">força mecânico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mechanical force</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2352">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PigLaunchingAndReceivingFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RuptureElement">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">rupture element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de ruptura</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000152">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">filtro grosso</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">strainer</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um filtro grosso é um artefato material que possui uma função de separação e tem um elemento filtrante, projetado para separar partículas sólidas de fluidos fazendo o fluido passar através de telas ou perfurações.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A strainer is a material artifact that bears a separation function and has a filtering element, designed to separate solid particles from fluids by passing the fluid through screens or perforations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;STRAINER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;STRAINING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device used to catch and hold the debris flowing in pipelines.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A filter that is separating solid particles from a fluid by passing the fluid through a wire mesh, screen or metal plates containing perforations or slits.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A mechanical separator that is separating solid particles from a fluid by passing the fluid through a wire mesh, screen or metal plates containing perforations or slits.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every strainer is a material artifact that bears a separation function and has a filtering element as component part at all times and participates in solid-liquid separation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3024"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Strainer(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SeparationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FilteringElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)) ∧ ∃p(SolidLiquidSeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ElectricalSignalPortion">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção elétrico de sinal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical signal portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000145">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A self operating valve that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RELIEF VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;PRESSURE RELIEF DEVICE&gt; that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A valve in a pressurized system that is set to open and relieve pressure at a certain pressure level.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A self operating valve that is set to open at a certain pressure level to prevent the pressure in a container or system from reaching unsafe levels.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A quick-acting, spring-loaded valve that opens to relieve pressure when the pressure exceeds the spring setting.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de alívio</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">relief valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every relief valve is a valve that bears a pressure relief function, which realizes a pressure relief process that automatically opens the valve when system pressure exceeds a predetermined setpoint.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2706"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ReliefValve(x) ↔ (Valve(x) ∧ ∃f (PressureReliefFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de alívio é uma válvula projetada para abrir automaticamente em um ponto de ajuste de pressão predeterminado para aliviar o excesso de pressão e prevenir níveis de pressão inseguros em um sistema.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A relief valve is a valve that is designed to automatically open at a predetermined pressure setpoint to relieve excess pressure and prevent unsafe pressure levels in a system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
