    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000254"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000257">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">DriveShaft ≡ Assembly ⊓ ∃bearerOf.PowerTransmissionFunction ⊓ ∃participatesIn.RotationalPowerTransferProcess</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DRIVE SHAFT&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENERGY TRANSFERRER&gt; that is a shaft used to transfer rotational power from a prime driver to several individual machines by use of drive belts and pulley wheels</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drive shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo de transmissão</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1102"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A drive shaft is an Assembly that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and consists in a shaft-based system used to transfer rotational mechanical energy from a prime mover to multiple driven machines.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um eixo de transmissão é um Assembly que possui uma PowerTransmissionFunction e consiste em um sistema baseado em eixo usado para transferir energia mecânica rotacional de um motor primário para múltiplas máquinas acionadas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DriveShaft(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(RotationalPowerTransferProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000205">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on vacuum reference chamber configuration. Under Open World Assumption, defining sufficient conditions could lead to unintended classification of complex instruments that contain vacuum chambers but serve different primary functions. The structural differentia is necessary but making it sufficient requires domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de pressão absoluta é um transmissor de pressão que possui uma câmara de referência de vácuo de um lado do sensor de pressão enquanto o outro lado recebe a pressão do processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An absolute pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that has a vacuum reference chamber on one side of the pressure sensor while the other side receives the process pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (AbsolutePressureTransmitter(x) → PressureTransmitter(x) ∧ ∃y (VacuumReferenceeChamber(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b7"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b5"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b6"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000144"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure transmitter where pressure is applied to one side of the sensor while the other side has a vacuum chamber.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ABSOLUTE PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; and an &lt;ABSOLUTE PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every absolute pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that has a vacuum reference chamber as a component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de pressão absoluta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">absolute pressure transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000120">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A valve with a sliding bar – common in the oilfield as tree valves.                  Gate valve is defined in API SPEC 6A as a valve assembly with a closure mechanism operating within the body, 90° to the conduit, to affect a closure. Gate valves are commonly used in the wellhead section of the well either as a side outlet valve in the spools or in the Christmas tree.                  Gate valves have two modes, either fully open or fully closed. This distinguish the gate valve from the chole valve. The gate valve will allow the fluid to follow or it will completely stop it. On the other hand, a choke valve will restrict the flow.                  Gate valves have several components including but not limited to:                  * Gate                  * Seat                  * Stem                  * Stem Packing (Seal)                  * Bearings                  * Grease fitting                  * Studs and nuts                  * Hand wheel</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of valve that incorporates a sliding gate to block fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GATE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; that is a valve where the closure member is a gate or disc with a linear motion parallel, or nearly parallel, to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gate valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula gaveta</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1686"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1687"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gate valve is a valve that has a gate closure component and a linear actuation mechanism.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GateValve(x) → (Valve(x) ∧ ∃g(GateClosure(g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g)) ∧ ∃m(LinearActuationMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions for structural features like 'linear sliding gate' risks false positives from complex hybrid equipment or custom manifolds that contain gate mechanisms but should not be classified as standard gate valves. Necessary conditions provide safer classification that can be validated by domain experts.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gate valve is a valve that has a gate or disc closure member with linear motion parallel to the plane of flat seats, which are transverse to the direction of flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula gaveta é uma válvula que possui um membro de fechamento tipo gaveta ou disco com movimento linear paralelo ao plano dos assentos planos, que são transversais à direção do fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000111">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1083"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1082"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DoubleBlockAndBleedValve(x) → (Valve(x) ∧ ∃p,s,b (PrimarySeat(p) ∧ SecondarySeat(s) ∧ BleedPort(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A double block and bleed valve is a valve that incorporates two seats each providing sealing capability and includes a means of venting the space between the seats.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de bloqueio duplo e sangria é uma válvula que incorpora duas sedes, cada uma proporcionando capacidade de vedação, e inclui um meio de ventilação do espaço entre as sedes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every double block and bleed valve is a valve that has a primary seat and has a secondary seat and has a bleed port.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive basis - the structural differentia (dual seats plus bleed port) defines necessary conditions, but under OWA we cannot assert that ANY artifact with these structural components is definitively a double block and bleed valve, as specialized multi-way valves or custom manifolds might contain similar mechanisms without being standard maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de bloqueio duplo e sangria</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">double block and bleed valve</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A block and bleed valve that is incorporating two seats, each of which provides a seal, and a means of venting the space between the seats. The seats may isolate with the pressure differential acting in the same or in opposite directions depending on the design.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DOUBLE BLOCK AND BLEED VALVE&gt; is a &lt;BLOCK AND BLEED VALVE&gt; and a &lt;DOUBLE BLOCK VALVE&gt; that is incorporating two seats, each of which provides a seal, and a means of venting the space between the seats. The seats may isolate with the pressure differential acting in the same or in opposite directions depending on the design</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PhysicalVariable">
