  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000268">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma prensa filtrante é um filtro que aplica força de compressão mecânica para melhorar a separação de substâncias através de um processo de filtração pressurizada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A filter press is a filter that applies mechanical compression force to enhance the separation of substances through a pressurized filtration process.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1306"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1308"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1309"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1307"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000081"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">prensa filtrante</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filter press</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FILTER PRESS&gt; is a &lt;FILTER&gt; and a &lt;PRESS(machine)&gt; intended to separate substance through compression</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A pressurized cell, fitted with a filter medium, used for evaluating filtration characteristics of a drilling fluid while it is either static or stirred.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Usually a DE filter.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is classified as 'both' functional and constructive. The structural differentia (pressure mechanism and compression process) involves specific mechanical configurations that are harder to make sufficient under Open World Assumption without detailed engineering specifications.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FilterPress(x) → Filter(x) ∧ ∃p(PressureMechanism(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃proc(MechanicalCompressionProcess(proc) ∧ participatesIn(x,proc)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every filter press is a filter that has a pressure mechanism as part and participates in mechanical compression processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SecondaryWinding">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">enrolamento secundário</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">secondary winding</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TransformerWinding"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000121">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An artefact that consists of a gear casing with an arrangement of two or more gear-wheels transmitting rotating motion from the input shaft to the output shaft.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GEARBOX&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; and that consistes of a gear casing with an arrangement of two or more gear-wheels transmitting rotating motion from the input shaft to the output shaft</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type because the structural differentia (specific gear casing and gear-wheel arrangement) is complex and making it sufficient under Open World Assumption could lead to false positives - specialized equipment containing gear mechanisms might be incorrectly classified as standard gearboxes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1722"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1724"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1723"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1721"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1725"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">caixa de engrenagens</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gearbox</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Gearbox(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c,g1,g2,i,o (GearCasing(c) ∧ GearWheel(g1) ∧ GearWheel(g2) ∧ g1≠g2 ∧ InputShaft(i) ∧ OutputShaft(o) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g1) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g2) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,o) ∧ ∃f (PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gearbox is an assembly that consists of a gear casing containing an arrangement of two or more gear-wheels that transmit rotating motion from an input shaft to an output shaft.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma caixa de engrenagens é um conjunto que consiste em um invólucro de engrenagens contendo um arranjo de duas ou mais rodas de engrenagem que transmitem movimento rotativo de um eixo de entrada para um eixo de saída.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gearbox is an assembly that has component parts including a gear casing, at least two gear-wheels, an input shaft, and an output shaft, and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1126">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PumpingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000265">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">junta de expansão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">expansion joint</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ExpansionJoint(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(ThermalExpansionAccommodationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃g(FlexibilityFunction(g) ∧ hasFunction(x,g))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] Flexible joint between two pipes to receive expansion from the pipes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device in a length of pipe that allows some pipe length expansion or contraction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;EXPANSION JOINT&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;JOINT&gt; that makes allowance for thermal expansion of the parts joined without distortion</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device or completion component designed to enable relative movement between two fixed assemblies in the event of thermal expansion or contraction.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An expansion joint is a material artifact that bears the designed function of accommodating thermal expansion and contraction between connected components through inherent flexibility while maintaining structural integrity.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma junta de expansão é um artefato material que possui a função projetada de acomodar expansão e contração térmica entre componentes conectados através de flexibilidade inerente, mantendo a integridade estrutural.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1239"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every expansion joint is a material artifact that bears a thermal expansion accommodation function and has a flexibility function, and every material artifact that bears a thermal expansion accommodation function and has a flexibility function is an expansion joint.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000169">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2758"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2702"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2703"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2757"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de alívio de pressão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pressure relief function</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1751">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] IMF purpose entity</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PUMP&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;PUMPING&gt; but may require parts and subsystems for that capability; including those turns it into a &lt;PUMP SYSTEM&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that adds or removes mechanical energy to a fluid, either constantly or periodically.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A machine that is capable of pumping but may require parts and subsystems for that capability.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba é um conjunto que possui a função projetada de adicionar energia mecânica ao fluido para pressurização e transporte.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pump is an assembly that bears the designed function of adding mechanical energy to fluid for pressurization and transport.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2646"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Pump(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f (PumpingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pump is an assembly that has the function of pumping fluid</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000229">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">chromatograph</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cromatógrafo</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHROMATOGRAPH&gt; is a &lt;PROCESS ANALYSER&gt; that analyses the molecular composition of a substance</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An analysing instrument that applies the principle of chromatography to analyse the molecular composition of a substance.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um cromatógrafo é um analisador de processo que possui uma função de análise cromatográfica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A chromatograph is a process analyzer that bears a chromatographic analysis function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b525"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every chromatograph is a process analyzer that has the function of chromatographic analysis.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Chromatograph(x) ↔ ProcessAnalyzer(x) ∧ ∃f (ChromatographicAnalysisFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/NoiseSilencingProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">noise silencing process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de silenciamento de ruído</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000141">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2549"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2548"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000086"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2547"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PowerTransformer(x) ↔ (Transformer(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalPowerTransformationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃r(ElectricalPowerTransmissionRole(r) ∧ bearerOf(x,r))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;POWER TRANSFORMER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSFORMER&gt; and an &lt;ELECTRIC POWER CONVERTER&gt; that, by electromagnetic induction, transforms a system of alternating voltage and current into another system of voltage and current usually of different values and at the same frequency for the purpose of transmitting electrical power</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A transformer that, by electromagnetic induction, transforms a system of alternating voltage and current into another system of voltage and current usually of different values and at the same frequency for the purpose of transmitting electrical power.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transformador de potência é um transformador que possui uma função de transformação de energia elétrica, realizada por indução eletromagnética para transformar sistemas de tensão e corrente alternadas para diferentes níveis na mesma frequência para fins de transmissão de energia.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A power transformer is a transformer that bears an electrical power transformation function, realized by electromagnetic induction to transform alternating voltage and current systems to different levels at the same frequency for power transmission purposes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transformador de potência</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">power transformer</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every power transformer is a transformer that has the function of transforming electrical power through electromagnetic induction, taking alternating current at one voltage level as input and producing alternating current at different voltage level(s) as output for power transmission.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000326">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pipeline</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">pipeline</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A fluid conductor that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A tube or system of tubes used for transporting crude oil and natural gas from the field or gathering system to the refinery.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] The principle underground transport of produced gas and oil.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A fluid conductor that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIPELINE&gt; is a &lt;CONTINOUS FLUID TRANSPORTER&gt; and a &lt;FLUID CONDUCTOR&gt; and a &lt;SYSTEM&gt; that consists of pipe, possibly also including pumps, valves, and control devices, intended for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Pipeline(x) ↔ EngineeredSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidTransportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um pipeline é um sistema engenheirado que possui uma função de transporte de fluidos, consistindo de tubos e possivelmente incluindo bombas, válvulas e dispositivos de controle, projetado para transportar líquidos, gases ou sólidos finamente divididos entre locais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pipeline is an engineered system that bears a fluid transport function, consisting of pipes and possibly including pumps, valves, and control devices, designed for conveying liquids, gases, or finely divided solids between locations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pipeline is an engineered system that bears a fluid transport function and has pipe as a component part at some time.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2428"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000199">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2551"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2556"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2543"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3174"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2550"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2544"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2555"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3173"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess and that consists in changing the voltage and current levels of electrical power through electromagnetic induction while maintaining power transfer efficiency.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an ElectricalPowerTransformationProcess and that consists in converting electrical energy from one voltage level to another through electromagnetic induction, enabling power distribution and utilization at appropriate voltage levels.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">electrical power transformation function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de transformação de energia elétrica</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2353">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000318"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2172">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidDistributionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000336">
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RotatingShaft"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2667"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pump shaft is a MaterialArtifact that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction, has impeller(s) as component parts, has bearings as component parts, and is part of a pump assembly.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um eixo de bomba é um MaterialArtifact que possui uma PowerTransmissionFunction e que é equipado com impulsor(es), mancais, buchas e elementos de vedação como parte de um conjunto de bomba para transmitir energia mecânica rotacional e possibilitar operações de bombeamento de fluidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pump shaft is a MaterialArtifact that bears a PowerTransmissionFunction and that is equipped with impeller(s), bearings, bushings, and sealing elements as part of a pump assembly for transmitting rotational mechanical energy to enable fluid pumping operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PumpShaft(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃i(Impeller(i) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,i)) ∧ ∃b(Bearing(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)) ∧ ∃p(Pump(p) ∧ partOf(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pump shaft</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">eixo de bomba</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration, sufficient conditions are omitted to avoid false positives under OWA. Any rotating component with an impeller and bearings could theoretically be classified as a pump shaft under sufficient conditions, including hybrid equipment or specialized assemblies that should not be automatically categorized as standard pump shafts.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PUMP SHAFT&gt; is a &lt;SHAFT&gt; of a pump that is provided with impeller(s), bearings, bushings, sealing elements etc.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/BottomHoleDrillingFunction">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de perfuração de fundo de poço</rdfs:label>
