  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000276">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLASH DRUM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VESSEL&gt; in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainer heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A tank or vessel in which a process stream is charged or pumped and where lighter products flash off or vaporize and are drawn off at the top. The remainder heavier fractions are drawn off at the bottom of the vessel.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um tambor de flash é um separador que realiza vaporização flash para separar componentes mais leves (que vaporizam e são retirados no topo) de componentes mais pesados (que permanecem líquidos e são retirados no fundo).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flash drum is a separator that performs flash vaporization to separate lighter components (which vaporize and are drawn off at the top) from heavier components (which remain liquid and are drawn off at the bottom).</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">tambor de flash</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flash drum</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1446"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlashDrum(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(FlashVaporizationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flash drum is a separator that bears a flash vaporization function and has a vapor outlet, liquid outlet, and feed inlet.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000232">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler that is intended to change a vapour to liquid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CONDENSER&gt; is a &lt;COOLER&gt; that has a capability of  &lt;CONDENSING&gt; a &lt;FLUID&gt; from &lt;VAPOUR&gt; to &lt;LIQUID&gt;</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Condenser(x) ↔ (HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃f(CondensationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b619"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um condensador é um trocador de calor que possui uma função projetada para condensar vapor em líquido removendo o calor latente de vaporização.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A condenser is a heat exchanger that bears a designed function to condense vapor to liquid by removing latent heat of vaporization.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">condensador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">condenser</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every condenser is a heat exchanger that bears a condensation function, and every heat exchanger that bears a condensation function is a condenser.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000092">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; is an &lt;EXCHANGER&gt; that has the capability of &lt;HEAT EXCHANGING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to transfer heat from one object to another.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">trocador de calor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heat exchanger</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1792"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A heat exchanger is a pressure vessel that bears the designed function of transferring thermal energy between two or more fluid streams while maintaining their separation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um trocador de calor é um vaso de pressão que possui a função projetada de transferir energia térmica entre duas ou mais correntes de fluido mantendo sua separação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (HeatExchanger(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(HeatTransferFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every heat exchanger is an assembly that has the function of heat transfer and has component parts including heat transfer surfaces and fluid passages for separated streams.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
