  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b544">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b546"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000348">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ShearRam(x) ↔ Ram(x) ∧ ∃f(PipeShearingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃b(ShearingBlade(b) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,b)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A blowout preventer (BOP) closing element fitted with hardened tool steel blades designed to cut the drillpipe or tubing when the BOP is closed, and then fully close to provide isolation or sealing of the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A shear valve is a ram-type BOP, similar in operation to a gate valve, but uses a pair of opposing steel plungers, rams. The rams extend toward the centre of the wellbore to restrict flow or retract open in order to permit flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A ram in the BOP that shears off the pipe.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAR RAM&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;RAM&gt; that is a closure mechanism on a wells blowout-preventer stack fitted with chisel-like jaws that are hydraulically operated. When the ram is closed on the pipe, the jaws or blades cut the pipe, permitting the upper section to be removed from the BOP stack</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">shear ram</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aríete de corte</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aríete de corte é um aríete que possui função de corte de tubulação e tem lâminas de corte endurecidas projetadas para cortar a coluna de perfuração ou tubulação durante operações de prevenção de blowout.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A shear ram is a ram that bears a pipe shearing function and has hardened cutting blades designed to cut drillpipe or tubing during blowout prevention operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2894"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every shear ram is a ram that has the function to shear pipe and has shearing blades as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b888">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DetectionFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2476">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PneumaticSeal"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000134">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula agulha</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">needle valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by specific structural features (needle plug geometry), providing sufficient conditions under the Open World Assumption could lead to over-classification. Complex valve assemblies or custom equipment containing needle-like mechanisms might be incorrectly classified as standard needle valves for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;NEEDLE VALVE&gt; is a &lt;GLOBE VALVE&gt; that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A globe valve that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A low volume, small orifice, high pressure bleed valve.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A globe valve that has a closure member with the shape of a conical plug (needle) which closes into a small seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of small valve used for flow metering, having a tapered needlepoint plug or closure element and a seat having a small orifice.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2250"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(NeedleValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y(NeedlePlug(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(SmallOrificeSeat(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula agulha é uma válvula que possui um membro de fechamento cônico em forma de agulha que se assenta em um pequeno orifício para fornecer controle preciso de fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A needle valve is a valve that has a conical needle-shaped closure member that seats into a small orifice to provide precise flow control.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every needle valve is a valve that has a needle plug component and has a small orifice seat component.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1327">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FiredHeatingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000255">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A process column intended to enable a distillation process</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DISTILLATION COLUMN&gt; is  a &lt;DISTILLATION SEPARATOR&gt; and a &lt;PROCESS COLUMN&gt; and a &lt;DISTILLER&gt; intended to enable a distillation process</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A process column intended to enable a distillation process.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma coluna de destilação é um separador que possui uma função de destilação para permitir a separação de misturas de fluidos baseada nas diferenças dos pontos de ebulição dos componentes através do equilíbrio vapor-líquido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A distillation column is a separator that bears a distillation function to enable separation of fluid mixtures based on differences in component boiling points through vapor-liquid equilibrium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">distillation column</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coluna de destilação</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DistillationColumn(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f (DistillationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every distillation column is a separator that has the function to perform distillation processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1049"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1596">
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1597"/>
