  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1977">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000375">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">well</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3408"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Well(x) ↔ EngineeredSystem(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceResourceInteractionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(Wellbore(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtSomeTime(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço é um sistema projetado que interage com recursos do subsolo através de um furo perfurado, projetado para obter, produzir, armazenar ou injetar materiais na terra ou a partir dela.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A well is an engineered system that interacts with subsurface resources through a drilled wellbore, designed to obtain, produce, store, or inject materials into or from the earth.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well is a collection of (zero or more) holes drilled into the Earth for the purpose of either (1) finding or producing underground resources; or (2) providing services related to the production of underground resources.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ppdm] A Well is a permitted or actual drilled hole in the ground designed to exchange (or facilitate the exchange of) fluids between a subsurface reservoir and the surface (or another reservoir), or to enable the detection and measurement of rock properties. Key concept: A physical Well is created each time the drill bit breaks the surface of the earth. Clarification: A Well is the parent of the Wellhead Stream(s), Well Origin, and all Well Components down hole from its Well Origin. A Well has a single Well Origin and all Wellbore(s) that extend from this Well Origin are parts of the Well. Re-entry through the same Well Origin for a Well that has not been plugged and abandoned does not create a new Well. A Well that has the same geographic coordinates as a previously existing plugged and abandoned, reclaimed or undrilled Well is a new Well. WB2-Cl2 Diagram Note: The Well depicted on page 3 groups multiple Well Components, including: one active Well WB2-C1 Origin (WO1), one inactive Wellbore (WB1), two active Wellbores (WB2, WB3), three inactive Wellbore Completions (WB1-C1, WB1-C2, WB1-C3) and three active Wellbore Completions (WB2-C1, WB3-C1, WB3-C2) and two active Wellbore Contact Intervals (WB2- CI1, WB2-CI2). ® Copyright 2014, PPDM Association. All Rights Reserved PAGE 4</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;WELL&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is arranged to obtain or produce from, or store or inject a material into, the earth</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every well is an engineered system that bears a subsurface resource interaction function and has a wellbore as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000119">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gate control valve is a control valve that uses a gate or wedge closure element moving perpendicular to the flow path to modulate fluid flow in response to control signals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de controle tipo gaveta é uma válvula de controle que usa um elemento de fechamento tipo gaveta ou cunha movendo-se perpendicular ao caminho do fluxo para modular o fluxo de fluido em resposta a sinais de controle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GATE CONTROL VALVE&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;CONTROL VALVE&gt; and a &lt;GATE VALVE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A control valve that is a gate valve and an actuated valve.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive subtype where the structural differentia (gate closure mechanism) defines necessary conditions. Under OWA, making this sufficient could force any assembly with a gate closure into this maintenance category, including specialized multi-way valves or custom manifolds that should not be classified as standard gate control valves.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de controle tipo gaveta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gate control valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1680"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1681"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000087"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GateControlValve(x) → ControlValve(x) ∧ ∃g(GateClosureMechanism(g) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,g)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gate control valve is a control valve that has a gate closure mechanism as component part at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1986">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InjectionProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3429">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WellheadSpool"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000124">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A heater is an assembly that bears a heating function to add thermal energy to a medium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aquecedor é um conjunto que possui uma função de aquecimento para adicionar energia térmica a um meio.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every heater is an assembly that bears a heating function and has heating elements and housing as component parts at all times</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">heater</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aquecedor</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Equipment that transfers heat to the produced gas stream.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HEATER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;HEATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An apparatus or machine that has the capability of heating.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1811"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Heater(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(HeatingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000066">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2669"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2668"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1126"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2742"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b926"/>
