  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000299">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1886"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1883"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1884"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1887"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000315"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1885"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor hidráulico é um motor que gera energia mecânica convertendo óleo hidráulico de alta pressão em movimento rotacional.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydraulic motor is a motor that generates mechanical energy by converting high pressure hydraulic oil to rotational motion.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(HydraulicMotor(x) → Motor(x) ∧ ∃f,p(HydraulicFluidPortion(f) ∧ hasInput(x,f) ∧ HydraulicToMechanicalEnergyConversionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydraulic motor is a motor that has hydraulic fluid input and participates in hydraulic-to-mechanical energy conversion process</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on hydraulic mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any device with hydraulic input might be misclassified as a hydraulic motor without domain expert validation of the complete structural requirements.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic motor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor hidráulico</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A motor that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A motor that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDRAULIC MOTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;MOTOR&gt; and a &lt;HYDRAULIC TO ROTATION ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is intended to generate power by means of high pressure oil</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000352">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every skid is an assembly that bears an equipment support function and has a support frame and mounting points as component parts at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A skid is an assembly that bears an equipment support function, consisting of a support frame and mounting points, designed to support equipment items during manufacturing, transportation, handling, and installation.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um skid é uma montagem que possui uma função de suporte de equipamento, consistindo de uma estrutura de suporte e pontos de montagem, projetada para suportar itens de equipamento durante fabricação, transporte, manuseio e instalação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Move a well to a close-by locations with minimum rig down of equipment.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A steel frame on which portable equipment is mounted to facilitate handling with cranes or flatbed trucks.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SKID&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SUPPORT&gt; intended to support items when being manufactured, transported, handled or installed</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A 'support' intended to support items when being manufactured, transported, handled or installed.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Skid(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EquipmentSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SupportFrame(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃m(MountingPoint(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">skid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">skid</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2960"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000217">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A boiler is a heater that brings a liquid to its boiling point through indirect contact heat exchange, producing steam or vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma caldeira é um aquecedor que leva um líquido ao seu ponto de ebulição através de troca de calor por contato indireto, produzindo vapor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">boiler</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">caldeira</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A that brings a liquid to its boiling point.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BOILER&gt; is a &lt;HEATER&gt; that brings a &lt;LIQUID&gt; to its boiling point</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An indirect contact heat exchanger that is intended to heat a liquid.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Boiler(x) ↔ Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(BoilingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every boiler is a heater that bears a BoilingFunction and has component parts including a steam drum and heat exchange surface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b286"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000076">
