  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000213">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every axial displacement transmitter is a transmitter that has the function to measure axial displacement and has as component part an axial displacement measuring probe.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">axial displacement transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de deslocamento axial</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An axial displacement transmitter is a transmitter that measures axial displacement and generates a standardized output signal representing the measured axial displacement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de deslocamento axial é um transmissor que mede deslocamento axial e gera um sinal de saída padronizado representando o deslocamento axial medido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(AxialDisplacementTransmitter(x) ↔ (Transmitter(x) ∧ ∃f(AxialDisplacementTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(AxialDisplacementMeasuringProbe(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b132"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;AXIAL DISPLACEMENT TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;DISPLACEMENT TRANSMITTER&gt; for &lt;AXIAL DISPLACEMENT&gt; measurement, using an &lt;AXIAL DISPLACEMENT MEASURING PROBE&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transmitter measuring an axial displacement and generating a standardized output signal representing the axial measured displacement.</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3141">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ThreePhaseSeparationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;ACTUATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;ACTUATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object for changing a signal into a corresponding movement.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] An actuator is a type of motor for moving or controlling a mechanism or system. Actuator's are a vital part of offshore operations.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A transducer that is intended to convert energy (electric, mechanical, pneumatic or hydraulic) from an external source into kinetic energy (motion) in response to a signal or or power input.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An actuator is an assembly that bears an actuation function to convert energy from an external source into kinetic motion in response to control signals.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um atuador é um conjunto que possui uma função de atuação para converter energia de uma fonte externa em movimento cinético em resposta a sinais de controle.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000207"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every actuator is an assembly that has the function of converting external energy into controlled kinetic motion.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b49"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Actuator(x) ↔ Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f (ActuationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">atuador</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">actuator</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1838">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/InterfacingFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de interfaceamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">interfacing function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2502"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2501"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in an InterfacingProcess and that consists in providing a standardized point of interface for communication, connection, or interaction with another object or system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ExhaustStack">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">chaminé de escapamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">exhaust stack</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2935">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/AcousticTreatmentElement"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2762">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000169"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000354">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">spacer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">espaçador</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SPACER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has the capability of &lt;SPACING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A viscous fluid used to aid removal of drilling fluids before a primary cementing operation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is intended to keep other physical objects at a predefined distance and hence having a spacer function.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In the context of pumping, a spacer is a fluid used between two fluids to prevent contamination.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2988"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A spacer is a material artifact that has the function of maintaining spatial separation or distance between physical objects or fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um espaçador é um artefato material que tem a função de manter separação espacial ou distância entre objetos físicos ou fluidos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every spacer is a material artifact that bears a spacing function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Spacer(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(SpacingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DrillingFluidPortion">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção de perfuração de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drilling fluid portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000100">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b368"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BUTTERFLY VALVE&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY VALVE&gt; that has a closure member of a disc type with a shaft parallel, or near parallel, to the plane of the disc, with an axis of rotation transverse to the flow direction</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A quick opening, low pressure valve, common on large openings through which solids will move, that allows high flow rate when open.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A rotary valve that has a closure member of a disc type with a shaft parallel, or near parallel, to the plane of the disc, with an axis of rotation transverse to the flow direction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary valve that has a closure member of a disc type with a shaft parallel, or near parallel, to the plane of the disc, with an axis of rotation transverse to the flow direction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A short face-to-face valve that has a movable vane in the center of the flow stream, which rotates 90° as the butterfly valve opens and closes.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">This is a constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under the Open World Assumption, any artifact with a disc-type closure and transverse rotation axis would be forced into the ButterflyValve class, including specialized hybrid equipment or custom manifolds containing butterfly mechanisms that should not be classified as standard butterfly valves for maintenance purposes.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ButterflyValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y(DiscTypeClosure(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(TransverseRotationAxis(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000100"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula borboleta</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">butterfly valve</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every butterfly valve is a valve that has a disc-type closure member and has a transverse rotation axis.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A butterfly valve is a valve that has a disc-type closure member with a shaft parallel to the plane of the disc and an axis of rotation transverse to the flow direction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula borboleta é uma válvula que possui um membro de fechamento tipo disco com haste paralela ao plano do disco e eixo de rotação transversal à direção do fluxo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1472">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FlowMeasurementProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3182">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TransformerCasing"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000108">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A membrane valve that is a membrane valve where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM VALVE&gt; is a &lt;MEMBRANE VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a resilient diaphragm being forced against a port</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b945"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b943"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b944"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Since this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism (diaphragm closure), necessary conditions are used to avoid over-classification under the Open World Assumption. Not every equipment with a diaphragm component should automatically be classified as a diaphragm valve - the structural differentia requires domain validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DiaphragmValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃d,p (ResilientDiaphragm(d) ∧ Port(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de diafragma é uma válvula que usa um diafragma resiliente forçado contra uma porta como seu mecanismo de fechamento para controlar o fluxo de fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm valve is a valve that uses a resilient diaphragm forced against a port as its closure mechanism to control fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm valve is a valve that has a resilient diaphragm as component part and has a port as component part and participates in diaphragm closure processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2668">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PumpingProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2874">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ShaftSleeve"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000107">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b570"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every coalescer is a separator that bears a coalescence function and participates in gravity separation processes to produce skimmable liquid portions.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Coalescer(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(CoalescenceFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(GravitySeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃o(SkimmableLiquidPortion(o) ∧ hasOutput(x,o))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COALESCER&gt; is a &lt;GRAVITY SEPARATOR&gt; where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A gravity separator where two liquid substances separates and where the substance with the less gravity can be skimmed off.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">coalescedor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">coalescer</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um coalescedor é um separador que usa meio de coalescência para promover a fusão de gotículas em misturas líquidas imiscíveis, permitindo separação por gravidade onde a fase líquida menos densa pode ser removida por escumação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A coalescer is a separator that uses coalescence media to promote droplet merger in immiscible liquid mixtures, enabling gravity-based separation where the less dense liquid phase can be skimmed off.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ContaminatedSurface">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">superfície contaminado</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">contaminated surface</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b787">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GasOutlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000371">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3343"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ValveSeat ⊑ MaterialArtifact ⊓ ∃partOf.Valve ⊓ ∃adjacentTo.ValveClosureMember ⊓ ∃bearerOf.SealingSurfaceQuality</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é parte de uma válvula e que fornece a superfície de assentamento contra a qual o membro de fechamento se apoia para alcançar o fechamento e controle do fluxo de fluido de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is part of a valve and that provides the seating surface against which the closure member bears to achieve shut-off and control of process fluid flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Valve seat is a constructive type defined by its structural configuration and interface role. Under the Open World Assumption, making this an equivalence class could lead to false positives where any artifact that is part of a valve and adjacent to a closure member gets classified as a valve seat, even if it serves a different structural role (such as guides, stops, or supports).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve seat</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">assento de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE SEAT&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; that is the part of a valve against which the closure member bears to provide shut-off and throughput of process fluids flows</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ValveSeat(x) → (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(Valve(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(ValveClosureMember(z) ∧ adjacentTo(x,z)) ∧ ∃q(SealingSurfaceQuality(q) ∧ bearerOf(x,q))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1930">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FiltrationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ActuationProcess">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which an actuator converts input energy (electrical, pneumatic, or hydraulic) into mechanical motion to operate valves, dampers, or other control devices.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which an actuator converts a control input signal to mechanical movement or force, enabling the positioning or operation of controlled equipment such as valves, dampers, or switches.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a control signal or energy input is converted by an actuator into mechanical motion or force that operates or positions another piece of equipment according to control requirements.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which an actuator converts input energy into controlled mechanical motion to operate valves, dampers, or other equipment requiring remote or automated positioning.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de atuação</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">actuation process</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000372">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ValveStem(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(ForceTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(ValveStemSeal(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3348"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3349"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">haste de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve stem</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Assembly that bears a ForceTransmissionFunction and that has a valve stem seal as a component part, specifically designed to transmit motion from a valve operator to the valve closure member.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Assembly que porta uma ForceTransmissionFunction e que tem um selo de haste de válvula como parte componente, especificamente projetado para transmitir movimento de um operador de válvula para o membro de fechamento da válvula.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">ValveStem SubClassOf Assembly and bearerOf some ForceTransmissionFunction and hasComponentPartAtAllTimes some ValveStemSeal</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE STEM&gt; is a &lt;VALVE COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;TRANSMITTER(force)&gt; that is a rod or shaft which is transmitting motion from an operator to the closure member of a valve</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by physical structure (rod/shaft mechanism). Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions would force any assembly with a valve stem seal and force transmission function to be classified as a valve stem, which could include complex multi-component assemblies, manifolds, or specialized valve mechanisms that contain these elements but should not be asserted into the standard valve stem maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1070">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DivertingProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
