  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000367">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3277"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3276"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3275"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3274"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3273"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">umbilical</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A device which is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An assembly of hydraulic hoses which can also include electrical cables or optic fibres, used to control a sub sea structure or remote operated vehicle from a platform or a vessel.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A control line attached to a remove piece of equipment, usually a subsea wellhead, to provide hydraulic or electrical control, or inject small amounts of chemicals.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;UMBILICAL&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is a flexible and easily disconnectable collection of cables and/or tubing for control, power, communication or chemical injection purposes.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An umbilical is an assembly that is a flexible and easily disconnectable bundle containing both cables and tubing for multi-service transmission including control, power, communication, and chemical injection.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um umbilical é uma montagem que é um feixe flexível e facilmente desconectável contendo cabos e tubulação para transmissão de múltiplos serviços incluindo controle, energia, comunicação e injeção química.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive basis requires necessary conditions only. Under OWA, any assembly with cables, tubing, flexibility, and disconnectability could be forcibly classified as umbilical, including specialized multi-service bundles, complex wiring harnesses, or custom transmission assemblies that contain these elements but serve different industrial contexts and maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Umbilical(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃c,t,s,conn (CableBundle(c) ∧ TubingBundle(t) ∧ ProtectiveSheathing(s) ∧ ConnectorAssembly(conn) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,conn) ∧ hasQuality(x,Flexibility) ∧ hasQuality(x,EasyDisconnectability)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every umbilical is an assembly that has component parts including cable bundles and tubing bundles, and has the qualities of flexibility and easy disconnectability.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000272">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um detector de chama é um detector que tem a função de detectar a presença de chamas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame detector is a detector that has the function to detect the presence of flames.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1365"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME DETECTOR&gt; is a &lt;DETECTOR&gt; and a &lt;FLAME DETECTING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;FLAME DETECTING MEASURING ELEMENT&gt; that is designed to detect the presence of a flame</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detector that is intended to sense a flame.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detector that is intended to sense a flame.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">detector de chama</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame detector</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameDetector(x) ↔ Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameDetectionFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame detector is a detector that has a flame detection function, and every detector that has a flame detection function is a flame detector.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000316">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that has a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that has a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A projecting short piece of pipe that is attached to another (hollow) body.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A shaped orifice for directing fluid flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;NOZZLE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;FLUID PORT&gt; and a &lt;CONNECTOR&gt; that is a protruding part through which a stream of fluid is directed</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A nozzle is a material artifact that has a protruding part with a shaped orifice designed to direct fluid flow into a specific pattern.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um bocal é um artefato material que possui uma parte protuberante com um orifício moldado projetado para direcionar o fluxo de fluido em um padrão específico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bocal</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">nozzle</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every nozzle is a material artifact that bears a fluid direction function and has a shaped orifice and protruding part as component parts.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Nozzle(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FluidDirectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃o(ShapedOrifice(o) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,o)) ∧ ∃p(ProtrudingPart(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2255"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1320">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000068"/>
