  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/KineticMotion">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">kinetic motion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">movimento cinético</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000283">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1607"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1610"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1609"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1608"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1611"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A gas cyclone separator is a separator that separates solid particles or liquid droplets from gas using centrifugal force generated by cyclonic flow geometry.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um separador ciclônico de gás é um separador que separa partículas sólidas ou gotículas líquidas do gás usando força centrífuga gerada pela geometria de fluxo ciclônico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every gas cyclone separator is a separator that has a cyclonic flow chamber as component part and participates in centrifugal separation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">separador ciclônico de gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas cyclone separator</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A static device generating centrifugal force from an incoming flow which separates solid or liquids from a gas of a different density.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by cyclonic mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any device with cyclonic flow chamber could be falsely classified as gas cyclone separator, including specialized multi-stage cyclones or hybrid separator designs that should not be forced into this standard maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (GasCycloneSeparator(x) → Separator(x) ∧ ∃y(CyclonicFlowChamber(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(CentrifugalSeparationProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b803">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DehumidificationProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000095">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A rotary valve that has a ball closure member.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;BALL VALVE&gt; is a &lt;ROTARY VALVE&gt; which uses a hollow, perforated or pivoting ball, of either "floating" design or "trunnion" mounted design to provide fluid flow control. The open position is when the ball hole is in line with the flow and closed when it is pivoted 90-degrees by the stem operator</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Any of several valves that rotate a ball with a flow passage to allow or deny flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A rotary valve that has a ball closure member.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve using a spherical closure element (ball) which is rotated through 90° to open and close the valve.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula esfera é uma válvula que controla o fluxo de fluidos usando um elemento de fechamento esférico que gira aproximadamente 90 graus para alinhar ou desalinhar sua passagem de fluxo com as portas do corpo da válvula.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A ball valve is a valve that controls fluid flow using a spherical ball closure member that rotates approximately 90 degrees to align or misalign its flow passage with the valve body ports.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b174"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b176"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b175"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000095"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical mechanism, sufficient conditions are omitted to avoid false positives under Open World Assumption. Complex multi-way valves or specialized equipment containing ball mechanisms should not be automatically classified as standard ball valves without domain expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ball valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula esfera</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every ball valve is a valve that has a ball closure component and participates in rotational motion processes</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(BallValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y(BallClosure(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(RotationalMotionProcess(z) ∧ participatesIn(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000359">
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification basis. The structural differentia (hollow cylindrical shape, positioning in process medium) is necessary but may not be sufficient under OWA - there could be other specialized parts of thermowells with similar geometry but different specific roles or configurations.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3136"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;THERMOWELL STEM&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;Feature&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; that is the hollow cylindrical part of a thermowell that is housing the thermocouple or thermoelement and is protruding into the process medium</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every thermowell stem is a fiat object part that is part of some thermowell and has hollow cylindrical shape and is located in process medium intrusion zone.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um termowell stem é uma parte de objeto fiducial que é parte de um termowell e que tem uma forma cilíndrica oca posicionada para se projetar no meio do processo, fornecendo habitação protetora para elementos de detecção de temperatura enquanto permite condução térmica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A thermowell stem is a fiat object part that is part of a thermowell and that has a hollow cylindrical shape positioned to protrude into the process medium, providing protective housing for temperature sensing elements while enabling thermal conduction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(ThermowellStem(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Thermowell(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃q(HollowCylindricalShape(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)) ∧ ∃l(ProcessMediumIntrusionZone(l) ∧ hasLocation(x,l)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">termowell stem</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">thermowell stem</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000335">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2662"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">carcaça de bomba</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pump casing</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PumpCasing(x) → Casing(x) ∧ ∃y(Impeller(y) ∧ surrounds(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(SuctionNozzle(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)) ∧ ∃w(DischargeNozzle(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical configuration. Under Open World Assumption, structural characteristics are harder to make sufficient - any assembly with an impeller and integral nozzles might be classified as a pump casing even if it serves a different specialized purpose. Starting with necessary conditions protects against false positives.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um invólucro que envolve um impulsor e possui bocais de sucção e descarga integrais como componentes estruturais, tipicamente aplicado em bombas centrífugas.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing that surrounds an impeller and has integral suction and discharge nozzles as structural components, typically applied in centrifugal pumps.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pump casing is a casing that surrounds an impeller and has integral suction and discharge nozzles forming part of its structure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PUMP CASING&gt; is a  &lt;CASING&gt; and a single wall surrounding the impeller. The suction and discharge nozzles form an integral part of the casing. Typically applied for centrifugal pumps</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ReciprocatingPistonMechanism">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reciprocating piston mechanism</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">mecanismo alternativo de pistão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000301">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1916"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1915"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000084"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1918"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1917"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1914"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um hidrociclone é um separador que separa misturas de fluidos usando forças centrífugas geradas por fluxo tangencial através de uma câmara cônica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hydrocyclone is a separator that separates fluid mixtures using centrifugal forces generated by tangential flow through a conical chamber.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hydrocyclone is a separator that has a conical section as component part at all times and participates in centrifugal separation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Hydrocyclone(x) ↔ Separator(x) ∧ ∃c(ConicalSection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)) ∧ ∃p(CentrifugalSeparationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HYDROCYCLONE&gt; is a &lt;CYCLONE&gt; and a &lt;CYLINDRICAL VESSEL&gt;, intended to separate a fluid by hydraulic forces</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] An item of solids-control equipment consisting of an inverted cone, the mud being fed tangentially into the upper (larger diameter) part.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cone shaped device for separating fluids and the solids dispersed in fluids.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">hidrociclone</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydrocyclone</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2952">
    <rdf:first rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000158"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2953"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/HydraulicFluid">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hydraulic fluid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fluido hidráulico</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000245">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um densitômetro é um instrumento que possui uma função de medição de densidade.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A densitometer is an instrument that bears a density measurement function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device installed on a mixing or pumping system manifold to measure the density of fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A device used for reading the density of a flowing fluid or slurry.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DENSITOMETER&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION ITEM&gt; and a &lt;MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; that measures the degree of darkness in photographic or semitransparent material. The densitometer is basically a light source aimed at a photoelectric cell which determines the density of the sample from differences in the readings</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b866"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">densitometer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">densitômetro</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every densitometer is an instrument that has the function of measuring density.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Densitometer(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(DensityMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000236">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A cooler and an air cooled heat exchanger that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A cooler and an air cooled heat exchanger that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COOLING TOWER&gt; is an &lt;AIR COOLED HEAT EXCHANGER&gt; and a &lt;TOWER&gt; that is a tall structure through which air circulates by convection</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b709"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CoolingTower(x) ↔ HeatExchanger(x) ∧ ∃t(Tower(t) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,t)) ∧ ∃p(ConvectiveAirCirculationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">torre de resfriamento</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">cooling tower</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every cooling tower is a heat exchanger that has a tower structure as component part at all times and participates in convective air circulation processes.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A cooling tower is a heat exchanger that incorporates a tall tower structure through which air circulates by convection to remove heat from process fluids.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma torre de resfriamento é um trocador de calor que incorpora uma estrutura de torre alta através da qual o ar circula por convecção para remover calor de fluidos de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000236"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000172">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2083"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000028"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2082"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2064"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2065"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level indication function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de indicação de nível</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3402">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000161"/>
