    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000256">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In the context of acidizing, a diverter is a material that forces acid to enter another zone by having a higher viscosity or building a filter cake.                  In the context of a wellhead, a diverter is a device in the flowpath at the wellhead that forces fluid to go down a pipe to a pit or tank.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIVERTER&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;DIVERTING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A chemical agent or mechanical device used in injection treatments, such as matrix stimulation, to ensure a uniform distribution of treatment fluid across the treatment interval.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A 'device' that is providing diversion of something from an expected course or direction.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Diverter(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(DivertingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diverter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">diverter</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diverter is a material artifact that bears a designed function to divert or redirect materials, fluids, or flows from their expected course to alternative paths or destinations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um diverter é um artefato material que possui uma função projetada para desviar ou redirecionar materiais, fluidos ou fluxos de seu curso esperado para caminhos ou destinos alternativos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diverter is a material artifact that has the function of diverting materials or flows from expected paths to alternative destinations.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1073"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LoggingData">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">logging data</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">dados de perfilagem</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000370">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que é uma parte componente de uma válvula e que é posicionado no fluxo para permitir, obstruir, desviar ou regular o fluxo através de posicionamento mecânico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that is a component part of a valve and that is positioned in the flow stream to permit, obstruct, divert or regulate flow through mechanical positioning.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every valve closure member is a material artifact that is a component part of some valve and participates in flow control processes by being positioned within the flow stream.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">As a constructive type defined by physical configuration and mechanical role, the valve closure member should use necessary conditions. The structural differentia (being positioned in flow stream) is harder to make sufficient under OWA - other components or hybrid devices might satisfy the conditions but not be classified as standard valve closure members.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3337"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">valve closure member</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">membro de fechamento de válvula</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (ValveClosureMember(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃v (Valve(v) ∧ isComponentPartOf(x,v)) ∧ ∃p (FlowControlProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)) ∧ ∃q (PositionableInFlowStream(q) ∧ hasQuality(x,q)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VALVE CLOSURE MEMBER&gt; is a &lt;CLOSURE&gt; that is the part of a valve which is positioned in the flow stream to permit, obstruct, divert or regulate flow</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FluidOpening">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">abertura de fluido</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fluid opening</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2789">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000034"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ReinforcedColumnShell">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">casco reforçado de coluna</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">reinforced column shell</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1183">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000342"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b188">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000197"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000374">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3378"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(VesselShell(x) → FiatObjectPart(x) ∧ ∃y(Vessel(y) ∧ partOf(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PressureContainmentFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fiat object part that is the outer pressure-containing structural boundary of a vessel, designed to enclose and isolate internal contents while withstanding internal pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma parte de objeto por fiat que é o limite estrutural externo de contenção de pressão de um vaso, projetada para encerrar e isolar o conteúdo interno enquanto suporta cargas de pressão interna.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;VESSEL SHELL&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;SHELL(structure)&gt; that is all or part of the pressure containing outer part of a vessel</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">vessel shell</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">parte de objeto por fiat</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">VesselShell SubClassOf: FiatObjectPart and partOf some Vessel and bearerOf some PressureContainmentFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type defined by structural configuration as outer pressure-containing part of vessel. Under Open World Assumption, sufficient conditions are difficult to establish - other structural components might also be pressure-containing parts of vessels in specialized designs.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
