  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000329">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2505"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Port(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(InterfacingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma InterfacingFunction e que é capaz de fornecer um ponto de interface para comunicação com outro objeto.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears an InterfacingFunction and that is capable of providing a point of interface for communication with another object.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PORT&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;PROVIDING&gt; a point of interface for communication with another object</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Port ≡ MaterialArtifact ⊓ ∃bearerOf.InterfacingFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma InterfacingFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">port</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000230">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um compensador é um artefato material que tem a função projetada de compensar movimento axial ou radial entre dois elementos conectados.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A compensator is a material artifact that has the designed function of compensating for axial or radial movement between two connected elements.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;COMPENSATOR&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that has a capability of &lt;COMPENSATING&gt; for axial or radial movement between two elements that is connected</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A device compensating for axial or radial movement between two elements that is connected.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every compensator is a material artifact that bears a movement compensation function and has component parts including a compensation mechanism and connection interfaces.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b584"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Compensator(x) ↔ MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(MovementCompensationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">compensator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">compensador</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000091">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Instrument(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(InstrumentationFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2009"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">instrument</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">instrumento</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um instrumento é um artefato material que tem a função projetada de realizar medição, monitoramento ou controle de variáveis de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An instrument is a material artifact that has the designed function to perform measurement, monitoring, or control of process variables.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[isa5_1] a device used for direct or indirect measurement, monitoring, and/or control of a variable, including primary elements, indicators, controllers, final control elements, computing devices, and electrical devices such as annunciators, switches, and pushbuttons.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every instrument is a material artifact that has an instrumentation function, and every material artifact that has an instrumentation function is an instrument.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b486">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PressureReductionProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
