  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000319">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A pig receiver is a vessel that has the function to receive pipe pigs from a pipeline.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um recebedor de pig é um vaso que tem a função de receber pigs de tubulação de um duto.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A chamber connected to the end of a pipeline intended for receiving pigs.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure vessel intended for receiving a pig from a pipeline.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PIG RECEIVER&gt; is a &lt;RECEIVER&gt; that is capable of &lt;RECEIVING&gt; a &lt;PIPE PIG&gt; from a pipeline</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every pig receiver is a vessel that bears a pig receiving function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (PigReceiver(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(PigReceivingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">recebedor de pig</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">pig receiver</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2332"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2793">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000168"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000123">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1750"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000077"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1749"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;GLOBE VALVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;VALVE&gt; where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A valve whose closure element is a flat disc or conical plug sealing on a seat that is usually parallel to the flow axis.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that is a valve where the closure member is a disc or piston operating with linear motion normal to the flat or shaped seat.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. Under OWA, making the structural differentia sufficient could force classification of specialized equipment containing linear motion closures (like complex multi-way valves or custom manifolds) as standard globe valves when they may warrant distinct maintenance categories.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">globe valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula globo</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every globe valve is a valve that has as component part at all times a linear motion closure and a normal seat.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(GlobeValve(x) → Valve(x) ∧ ∃y,z(hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y) ∧ LinearMotionClosure(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z) ∧ NormalSeat(z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula globo é uma válvula caracterizada por um elemento de fechamento (disco ou tampão) que opera com movimento linear perpendicular a uma sede orientada normal ao caminho do fluxo do fluido.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A globe valve is a valve characterized by a closure member (disc or plug) that operates with linear motion perpendicular to a seat that is oriented normal to the fluid flow path.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1698">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000112">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that is intended for subsurface control/check operation.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DOWN HOLE SAFETY VALVE&gt; is a &lt;SAFETY VALVE&gt; that is intended for subsurface control/check operation</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DownHoleSafetyValve(x) ↔ SafetyValve(x) ∧ ∃f(SubsurfaceSafetyFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(SubsurfaceOperationProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1088"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every down hole safety valve is a safety valve that bears a SubsurfaceSafetyFunction and participates in SubsurfaceOperationProcess</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">down hole safety valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de segurança de fundo de poço</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A down hole safety valve is a safety valve that bears a subsurface safety function for pressure relief and flow control operations in wellbore or other subsurface environments.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de segurança de fundo de poço é uma válvula de segurança que possui uma função de segurança subsuperficial para operações de alívio de pressão e controle de fluxo em poços ou outros ambientes subsuperficiais.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2452">
