  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A valve that permits fluid to flow in one direction only.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A valve that permits fluid to flow in one direction only.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A valve that only allows flow in one direction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A mechanical device that permits fluid to flow or pressure to act in one direction only.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CHECK VALVE&gt; is a &lt;VALVE&gt; that permits fluid to flow in one direction only</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma válvula de retenção é uma válvula que possui uma função de prevenção de refluxo, permitindo automaticamente que o fluido flua em apenas uma direção enquanto previne o fluxo reverso.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A check valve is a valve that bears a backflow prevention function, automatically permitting fluid to flow in one direction only while preventing reverse flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">check valve</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">válvula de retenção</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CheckValve(x) ↔ Valve(x) ∧ ∃f(BackflowPreventionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b453"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every check valve is a valve that has the function to prevent backflow and automatically allow unidirectional fluid flow.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000103"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DrillingFluid">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">drilling fluid</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">fluido de perfuração</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b382">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b386"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b74">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000004"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000305">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um poço de injeção é um poço que possui a função projetada de injetar materiais em um reservatório a uma pressão superior à pressão da formação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An injection well is a well that bears the designed function of injecting materials into a reservoir at pressure higher than formation pressure.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A well in which fluids are injected rather than produced, the primary objective typically being to maintain reservoir pressure.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A well either specifically drilled, or, more likely, a poor producer that is converted to inject fluids to stabilize the decline of pressure in a productive zone. An injector is required to have a pressure connection to the pay and to a producing well. Water is typically injected at the base of the pay or, in a gas well, or gas is injected into the gas cap.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INJECTION WELL&gt; is  a &lt;WELL&gt; with the purpose of injecting a material into a reservoir, normally with a pressure higher than the formation pressure</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1990"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every injection well is a well that has the function to inject materials into a reservoir under pressure.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">poço de injeção</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">injection well</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (InjectionWell(x) ↔ (Well(x) ∧ ∃f (InjectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000313">
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every mill is an assembly that has the function to process materials, and every assembly that has the function to process materials is a mill.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um moinho é um conjunto que possui uma função de processamento de material para reduzir o tamanho de partículas ou modificar materiais sólidos através de operações mecânicas de moagem, corte ou trituração.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A mill is an assembly that bears a material processing function to reduce particle size or modify solid materials through mechanical grinding, cutting, or crushing operations.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">moinho</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mill</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2193"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;MILL&gt; is a &lt;FACILITY&gt; that consists of the land, buildings, machinery, apparatus, and fixtures, mostly employed in &lt;MANUFACTURING&gt; of discrete &lt;COMMODITY MATERIAL&gt;s</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A mill is usually used to remove junk in the hole or to grind away all or part of a casing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A cutting tool used to grind up metal, dress off a fish, or open up a window for a kick-off.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Mill(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(MaterialProcessingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/PositionSensor">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sensor de posição</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">position sensor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b848">
    <owl:intersectionOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b852"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000349">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A grooved pulley.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SHEAVE&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;WHEEL&gt; which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] In oilfield usage, the term usually refers to either the pulleys permanently mounted on the top of the rig (the crown blocks), or the pulleys used for running wireline tools into the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A wheel which is grooved for use with vee-belts, ropes, round belts, wire or pipe.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2906"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2908"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2907"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sheave</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">polia</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive type based on physical structure. Under OWA, defining sufficient conditions based solely on having a grooved rim could lead to false positives where other grooved mechanical elements (like timing belt pulleys with different design intents) are automatically classified as sheaves. The structural differentia provides necessary conditions while allowing domain experts to confirm sufficient conditions.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A sheave is a material artifact that is a grooved wheel designed to transmit mechanical power through interface with belts, ropes, wires, or pipes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma polia é um artefato material que é uma roda sulcada projetada para transmitir energia mecânica através da interface com correias, cordas, cabos ou tubos.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every sheave is a material artifact that has a grooved rim as component part and bears a power transmission function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Sheave(x) → MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃y(GroovedRim(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃f(PowerTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b463">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/EnclosureProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2082">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/LevelIndicationProcess"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2158">
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2153"/>
    <rdf:rest rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2159"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/StructuralSupportProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de suporte estrutural</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">structural support process</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural element bears loads, distributes forces, or maintains structural integrity within a system, typically through its geometric configuration and material properties.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1200">
    <rdf:rest rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#nil"/>
    <rdf:first rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1198"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2707">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000169"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000125">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">humidity analyser</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">analisador de umidade</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A meter intended to measure and indicate and/or produce a signal which represents the measured humidity.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every humidity analyser is a process analyzer that has the function to measure humidity content.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A humidity analyser is an instrument designed to measure and indicate humidity or moisture content in process streams or environments.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um analisador de umidade é um analisador de processo que é projetado para medir e indicar o conteúdo de umidade ou vapor d'água em correntes de processo ou ambientes.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1848"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (HumidityAnalyser(x) ↔ ProcessAnalyzer(x) ∧ ∃f (HumidityMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ hasFunction(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000201">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3133"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3124"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3132"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3123"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de proteção de sensor de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature sensor protection function</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A DesignedFunction that is realized in a TemperatureSensorProtectionProcess and that consists in providing a protective enclosure for temperature sensing elements while enabling thermal conductivity from the process medium to the sensor.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3019">
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SeparationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000351">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A silo is a vessel that bears a solid bulk storage function and has a conical bottom section for facilitating the storage and discharge of bulk solid materials.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um silo é um vaso que possui uma função de armazenamento de sólidos a granel e tem uma seção inferior cônica para facilitar o armazenamento e descarga de materiais sólidos a granel.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">silo</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">silo</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SILO&gt; is a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; with a conical shape that is intended to store solids in bulk</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A vessel that has a bottom in the shape of a cone and is intended to store solid particles.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] A with a conical shape that is intended to store solids in bulk (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every silo is a vessel that has the function of storing bulk solids and has a conical bottom component.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2948"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (Silo(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(SolidBulkStorageFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃c(ConicalBottom(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000250">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIESEL ENGINE&gt; is  an &lt;INTERNAL COMBUSTION ENGINE&gt; and a &lt;RECIPROCATING PISTON ENGINE&gt; in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An internal combustion engine in which ignition of the fuel injected into the cylinder is performed by the heat of compression of the air charge.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diesel engine</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">motor diesel</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b971"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b968"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b970"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b967"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b969"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000264"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um motor diesel é um motor que inflama combustível através do calor de compressão em vez de ignição por centelha, requerendo sistemas de ignição por compressão e injeção de combustível.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diesel engine is an engine that ignites fuel through compression heat rather than spark ignition, requiring compression ignition and fuel injection systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">A diesel engine is necessarily an engine that has compression ignition system and fuel injection system and participates in compression ignition process.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions for this constructive type. While compression ignition is characteristic of diesel engines, under OWA we cannot be certain that any engine with compression ignition systems is necessarily a diesel engine - there could be hybrid or specialized engines with similar mechanisms that should not be auto-classified as standard diesel engines without expert validation.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">DieselEngine(x) → Engine(x) ∧ ∃s(CompressionIgnitionSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃f(FuelInjectionSystem(f) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(CompressionIgnitionProcess(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000109">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">manômetro de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure gauge</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b979"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE GAUGE&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; using a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING ELEMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A gauge that is intended for measuring and indicating pressure differences.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DifferentialPressureGauge(x) ↔ PressureGauge(x) ∧ ∃f(DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)) ∧ ∃p(PressurePortPair(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um manômetro de pressão diferencial é um manômetro que mede e indica a diferença entre duas entradas de pressão usando um elemento de medição de pressão diferencial.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure gauge is a pressure gauge that measures and indicates the difference between two pressure inputs using a differential pressure measuring element.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure gauge is a pressure gauge that bears a DifferentialPressureMeasurementFunction and has component parts including a DifferentialPressureMeasuringElement and PressurePortPair.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1680">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000027"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ContainmentProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">containment process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de contenção</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a container artifact encloses and maintains internal components or fluids within its structural boundaries, providing physical separation from the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which material is enclosed and retained within a defined spatial boundary by a containing artifact.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a structural boundary maintains separation between internal contents and external environment, preventing uncontrolled release while withstanding internal pressure loads.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/RamBody">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">ram body</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">corpo de aríete</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1633">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ReciprocatingPistonMechanism"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/Sensor">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sensor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">sensor</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A casing is an assembly that provides structural enclosure with pressure containment capability, characterized by walls that separate internal components or fluids from the external environment.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um casing é um conjunto que fornece invólucro estrutural com capacidade de contenção de pressão, caracterizado por paredes que separam componentes internos ou fluidos do ambiente externo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Casing(x) → Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(EnclosureFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃w(CasingWall(w) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,w)) ∧ ∃p(PressureContainmentFunction(p) ∧ hasFunction(x,p)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b400"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b398"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b399"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/Assembly"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Large-diameter pipe lowered into an openhole and cemented in place.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] One of several strings of steel pipe in a well design that, together with cement, forms a barrier to fluid movement along the drilled hole. It is commonly at least partly cemented in the wellbore.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CASING&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ENCLOSURE&gt; that is the stationary enclosure of a machine intended to contain a fluid and equipment internals</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An enclosure that can maintain a pressure difference.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">casing</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">casing</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every casing is an assembly that has an enclosure function and has component part some casing wall and has function some pressure containment function.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on structural configuration. Under OWA, sufficient conditions for enclosure structure could lead to over-classification of complex assemblies that contain enclosure elements but serve different primary functions (e.g., pressure vessels, housings, containers).</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000222"/>
  </rdf:Description>
