  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000295">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">hopper</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">hopper</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] The device used to facilitate the addition of drilling fluid additives to the whole mud system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A vessel with a conical shape for filling or dosing purposes.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;HOPPER&gt; is a &lt;CONTAINER&gt; with a conical shape that is intended to store solids for filling or dosing purposes</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Mixing chamber where dry components can be evenly mixed with liquids. The dry materials are introduced at the bottom of the hopper through a nozzle.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A hopper is a vessel that is designed to store solid materials and dispense them through a controlled discharge opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um hopper é um vaso projetado para armazenar materiais sólidos e dispensá-los através de uma abertura de descarga controlada.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Hopper(x) ↔ (Vessel(x) ∧ ∃f(SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(SolidDischargeOpening(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1822"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every hopper is a vessel that bears a SolidStorageAndDispensingFunction and has a SolidDischargeOpening as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureSensorProtectionProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de proteção de sensor de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature sensor protection process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A PlannedProcess in which a protective barrier shields a temperature sensing element from direct contact with the process medium while maintaining thermal conductivity to enable accurate temperature measurement.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000249">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000337"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b931"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b932"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b930"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIAPHRAGM PUMP&gt; is a &lt;RECIPROCATING PUMP&gt; intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere; flow rate is achieved through reciprocatory motion of the diaphragm</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A reciprocating pump intended to pump a liquid with a small capacity. This is done by means of thin flexible diaphragms to seal pumped fluid from leakage to atmosphere.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that has flexible diaphragm as component part at all times and participates in diaphragm sealing.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba de diafragma</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">diaphragm pump</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(DiaphragmPump(x) → (ReciprocatingPump(x) ∧ ∃d(FlexibleDiaphragm(d) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,d)) ∧ ∃p(DiaphragmSealing(p) ∧ participatesIn(x,p))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A diaphragm pump is a reciprocating pump that uses flexible diaphragms to displace liquid and seal the pumped fluid from atmospheric leakage.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba de diafragma é uma bomba alternativa que usa diafragmas flexíveis para deslocar líquido e selar o fluido bombeado contra vazamento atmosférico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Using necessary conditions because this is a constructive type defined by physical mechanism. Under OWA, any pump with a flexible diaphragm component could be classified as a diaphragm pump, but there may be hybrid or specialized equipment containing diaphragms that should not be automatically classified into this maintenance category.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
  </rdf:Description>
