  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000188">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de medição e transmissão de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature measurement and transmission function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3106"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3107"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/DesignedFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000365">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma cabeça de coluna é um componente de cabeça de poço que suporta o suspensor de coluna e fornece uma interface de conexão para fixar a árvore de natal ao conjunto de cabeça de poço.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A tubing head is a wellhead component that supports the tubing hanger and provides a connection interface for attaching the Christmas tree to the wellhead assembly.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">cabeça de coluna</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing head</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A wellhead component that supports the tubing hanger and provides a means of attaching the Christmas tree to the wellhead.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TUBING HEAD&gt; is a &lt;DRILLING COMPONENT&gt; that is fixed to the top of the tubing set in a well.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A flanged spool containing the tubing bowl where the tubing hanger will set and seal.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3234"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TubingHead(x) ↔ WellheadComponent(x) ∧ ∃f(TubingSupportAndConnectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p1(TubingBowl(p1) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p1)) ∧ ∃p2(ChristmasTreeConnectionInterface(p2) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p2)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every tubing head is a wellhead component that bears a tubing support and connection function, has a tubing bowl as component part, and has a Christmas tree connection interface as component part.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1089">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000170"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000270">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FiredHeater(x) ↔ (Heater(x) ∧ ∃f(FiredHeatingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FIRED HEATER&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;HEATER&gt; in which the heat converted from burning solids, liquids or gas is transferred to a media</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] Is a fired heat transfer equipment intended to burn fuel and to transfer the heat of combustion to a liquid without vaporising the liquid.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A fired heater is a heater that burns fuel (solid, liquid, or gas) to generate heat for transfer to a process fluid medium.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um aquecedor a combustão é um aquecedor que queima combustível (sólido, líquido ou gasoso) para gerar calor para transferência para um fluido de processo.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">aquecedor a combustão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">fired heater</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1334"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every fired heater is a heater that bears a FiredHeatingFunction</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2934">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/SilencerHousing"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
