  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000127">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A visible sign of a chemical reaction.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] An artefact that is a intended to display the value or the status of a condition.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] In a chemical context, an indicator is a chemical in a titration reaction that changes color at a certain pH.                  In the context of a mechanical load, an indicator is a dial or gauge.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] An &lt;INDICATOR&gt; is an &lt;INSTRUMENTATION FUNCTION&gt; that has a capability of &lt;INDICATING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">indicator</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">indicador</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every indicator is an instrument that bears an indication function to display process information in human-perceptible form.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An indicator is an instrument that displays or shows the value or status of a measured variable or condition to make it perceptible to operators.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um indicador é um instrumento que exibe ou mostra o valor ou status de uma variável medida ou condição para torná-la perceptível aos operadores.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Indicator(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(IndicationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1961"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000085">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2924"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um Instrumento que porta uma VisualInspectionFunction e que consiste em uma interface de visualização transparente que permite observação óptica direta de condições internas, propriedades de fluidos ou estados de processo dentro de recipientes, vasos ou sistemas de tubulação.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">An Instrument that bears a VisualInspectionFunction and that consists in a transparent viewing interface that enables direct optical observation of internal conditions, fluid properties, or process states within containers, vessels, or piping systems.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;SIGHT GLASS&gt; is a &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; whose purpose is to enable seeing the internals of a &lt;CONTAINER&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A physical object that is transparent and intended for viewing a vessel or piping system interior.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every sight glass is an instrument that bears a visual inspection function and enables direct optical observation of process internals through a transparent viewing interface.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">visor</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">sight glass</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(SightGlass(x) ↔ Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(VisualInspectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1725">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000317"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1263">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:allValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/FiltrationProcess"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000054"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000083">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A&lt;FLOW MODIFICATION ACCESSORY&gt; is a &lt;FINAL CONTROL ASSEMBLY COMPONENT&gt; and a &lt;MODIFIER&gt; that is used to modify the characteristics of fluid flow</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and that is used as a component in flow control assemblies to alter the characteristics of fluid flow such as velocity profile, turbulence, or pressure distribution.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um MaterialArtifact que possui uma FlowModificationFunction e que é usado como componente em conjuntos de controle de fluxo para alterar as características do fluxo de fluido, como perfil de velocidade, turbulência ou distribuição de pressão.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow modification accessory</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">MaterialArtifact que possui uma FlowModificationFunction e</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow modification accessory is a MaterialArtifact that bears a FlowModificationFunction and participates in processes that alter fluid flow characteristics.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1525"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowModificationAccessory(x) ↔ (MaterialArtifact(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowModificationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b622">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/CondensateOutlet"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/TemperatureElement">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detecting element intended to sense temperature.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A detecting element intended to sense temperature.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de temperatura é um instrumento que possui uma função de sensoreamento de temperatura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A temperature element is an instrument that bears a temperature sensing function.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">temperature element</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de temperatura</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3072"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every temperature element is a detecting element that has the function to sense temperature</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TemperatureElement(x) ↔ DetectingElement(x) ∧ ∃f(TemperatureSensingFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b456">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000227"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasComponentPartAtAllTimes"/>
