  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000110">
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1018"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A differential pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that bears a differential pressure transmission function, enabling it to measure the pressure difference between two input pressure signals and transmit this difference as a standardized output signal.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transmissor de pressão diferencial é um transmissor de pressão que possui uma função de transmissão de pressão diferencial, permitindo medir a diferença de pressão entre dois sinais de pressão de entrada e transmitir essa diferença como um sinal de saída padronizado.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every differential pressure transmitter is a pressure transmitter that bears a differential pressure transmission function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; is a &lt;PRESSURE TRANSMITTER&gt; and a &lt;DIFFERENTIAL PRESSURE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A pressure transmitter that is producing a standardized output signal dependent of a received pressure difference signal.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transmissor de pressão diferencial</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">differential pressure transmitter</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (DifferentialPressureTransmitter(x) ↔ PressureTransmitter(x) ∧ ∃f (DifferentialPressureTransmissionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2925">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/VisualInspectionFunction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalEnergyPortion">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mechanical energy portion</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">porção mecânico de energia</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000137">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(PhaseSequenceMeter(x) ↔ ElectricMeasuringInstrument(x) ∧ ∃f(PhaseSequenceMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(PolyphaseElectricalSignal(s) ∧ hasInput(x,s)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A phase sequence meter is an electric measuring instrument that bears a phase sequence measurement function to determine and indicate the sequence in which the instantaneous voltages of phase conductors reach their maximum value in a polyphase electrical system.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um medidor de sequência de fases é um instrumento de medição elétrica que possui uma função de medição de sequência de fases para determinar e indicar a sequência na qual as tensões instantâneas dos condutores de fase atingem seu valor máximo em um sistema elétrico polifásico.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">phase sequence meter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">medidor de sequência de fases</rdfs:label>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;PHASE SEQUENCE METER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC VARIABLE MEASURING INSTRUMENT&gt; that indicates, on a polyphase system, the sequence in which the instantaneous voltage of the phase conductors reach their maximum value</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every phase sequence meter is an electric measuring instrument that has the function to measure phase sequence and has as input polyphase electrical signals.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2299"/>
  </rdf:Description>
