  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/GasDetectionFunction">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">função de detecção de gás</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">gas detection function</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1615"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1616"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/DetectionFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000128">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A level element is an instrument that bears a level detection function for determining fluid level in a vessel or container.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de nível é um instrumento que possui uma função de detecção de nível para determinar o nível de fluido em um vaso ou recipiente.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detecting element that is intended to determine a level.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every level element is a detector that has the function to detect fluid level</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x (LevelElement(x) ↔ Detector(x) ∧ ∃f(LevelDetectionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2054"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de nível</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">level element</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/ThermalExpansionAccommodationProcess">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">thermal expansion accommodation process</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">processo de acomodação de expansão térmica</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/PlannedProcess"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000364">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A device attached to the topmost tubing joint in the wellhead to support the tubing string.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A well string hanger that is used for production tubing. The tubing hanger incorporates a sealing system to ensure that the tubing conduit and annulus are hydraulically isolated.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] A slip set or donut that suspends and holds the top of the tubing in the wellhead.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TUBING HANGER&gt; is a &lt;WELL STRING HANGER&gt; that is installed on top of the tubing string and supports the string when landed in the tubing hanger or tubing head.</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3213"/>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(TubingHanger(x) ↔ (Assembly(x) ∧ ∃f(TubingSupportFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃s(SealingSystem(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃m(SupportMechanism(m) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,m)) ∧ ∃c(TubingConnection(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um suporte de coluna de produção é um conjunto que suporta colunas de produção em cabeças de poço com vedação integrada para isolar o conduto da coluna do anular.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A tubing hanger is an assembly that supports tubing strings in wellheads with integrated sealing to isolate tubing conduit from annulus.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every tubing hanger is an assembly that bears a tubing support function and has component parts including a sealing system, support mechanism, and tubing connection.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">tubing hanger</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">suporte de coluna de produção</rdfs:label>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1420">
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/WasteGasDisposalFunction"/>
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/hasFunction"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Restriction"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/MechanicalPort">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">mechanical port</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bocal mecânico</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/construct/MaterialArtifact"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000102">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000072"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b430"/>
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b429"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">centrifugal pump</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">bomba centrífuga</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:isPrimitive rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</iof-av:isPrimitive>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A dynamic pump that contains impellers provided with vanes to generate centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;CENTRIFUGAL PUMP&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and a &lt;PUMP&gt; in which centrifugal force imparted by impeller is convered to pressure in the volute casing. NOTE - Combine with either  BARE PUMP or PUMP SYSTEM,</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[OnePetro] Pump with an impeller or rotor that spins in a housing and the drag forces on the fluids cause them to flow.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A type of pump commonly used in the handling and mixing of oilfield fluids.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A dynamic pump utilizing impellers provided with vanes generating centrifugal force to achieve the required pressure head.</skos:definition>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A centrifugal pump is a pump that uses centrifugal force generated by rotating impellers with vanes to increase fluid pressure through a volute casing.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Uma bomba centrífuga é uma bomba que usa força centrífuga gerada por impulsores rotativos com pás para aumentar a pressão do fluido através de uma carcaça voluta.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <skos:exactMatch rdf:resource="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000102"/>
    <iof-av:primitiveRationale xml:lang="en">Constructive classification based on physical mechanism. Under Open World Assumption, any equipment with centrifugal impellers and volute casing could be inferred as a standard centrifugal pump, potentially misclassifying specialized hybrid equipment or complex pump systems that contain centrifugal stages but serve different operational roles.</iof-av:primitiveRationale>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(CentrifugalPump(x) → Pump(x) ∧ ∃y(CentrifugalImpeller(y) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,y)) ∧ ∃z(VoluteCasing(z) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,z)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every centrifugal pump is a pump that has a centrifugal impeller as component part at all times and has a volute casing as component part at all times.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
