  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000081">
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Filter(x) ↔ (Separator(x) ∧ ∃f(FiltrationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃e(FilterElement(e) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,e)) ∧ ∃h(FilterHousing(h) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,h))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A separator intended to remove solids from vapour or liquid.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] Devices for selecting or excluding data from a data stream or dataset.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FILTER&gt; is a  &lt;FunctionalObject&gt; that is capable of &lt;FILTERING&gt;</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[SLB Glossary] A process or algorithm using a set of limits used to eliminate unwanted portions of seismic data, commonly on the basis of frequency or amplitude, to enhance the signal-to-noise ratio of the data or to achieve deconvolution.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[DEXPI] An apparatus or machine that is capable of filtering (from ``_).</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A separator intended to remove solids from vapour or liquid</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1268"/>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">filter</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">filtro</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every filter is a separator that has a filtration function and has a filter element as component part and has a filter housing as component part</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um filtro é um separador que possui uma função de filtração para remover seletivamente constituintes indesejados de um fluxo de fluido usando um elemento filtrante dentro de um alojamento de filtro.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A filter is a separator that bears a filtration function to selectively remove unwanted constituents from a fluid stream using a filter element within a filter housing.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000271">
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um arrestador de chama é um dispositivo de segurança que possui uma função de arrestar chama para prevenir que chamas entrem em um sistema através de uma abertura.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flame arrestor is a safety device that bears a flame arrest function to prevent flames from entering a system through an opening.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">arrestador de chama</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flame arrestor</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlameArrestor(x) ↔ SafetyDevice(x) ∧ ∃f(FlameArrestFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flame arrestor is a safety device that has the function of arresting flames and processes gaseous portions while preventing flame propagation.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] An arrestor which is a trap over an opening, e.g. of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;FLAME ARRESTOR&gt; is an &lt;ARTEFACT&gt; and an &lt;ARRESTOR&gt; that is a trap covering an opening, e.g of a ventilation system or a pipe, to prevent flames from entering the system</skos:definition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1350"/>
  </rdf:Description>
  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000086">
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A physical object that transforms continuous currents from one voltage to another, or continuous into alternating currents or vice versa.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;TRANSFORMER&gt; is an &lt;ELECTRIC TO ELECTRIC ENERGY CONVERTER&gt; that is capable of &lt;TRANSFORMING&gt; power from one circuit to another without changing frequency and works on the principle of mutual induction</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A transformer that, by electromagnetic induction, transforms a system of alternating voltage and current into another system of voltage and current usually of different values and at the same frequency for the purpose of transmitting electrical power.</skos:definition>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">transformer</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">transformador</rdfs:label>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b3177"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every transformer is an electrical equipment that bears an electrical power transformation function and has component parts including primary winding, secondary winding, and magnetic core.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A transformer is an electrical equipment that transforms electrical power from one circuit to another at the same frequency through electromagnetic induction using windings and a magnetic core.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um transformador é um equipamento elétrico que transforma energia elétrica de um circuito para outro na mesma frequência através de indução eletromagnética usando enrolamentos e um núcleo magnético.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(Transformer(x) ↔ ElectricalEquipment(x) ∧ ∃f(ElectricalPowerTransformationFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)) ∧ ∃p(PrimaryWinding(p) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,p)) ∧ ∃s(SecondaryWinding(s) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,s)) ∧ ∃c(MagneticCore(c) ∧ hasComponentPartAtAllTimes(x,c)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
  </rdf:Description>
