  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000146">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">restriction orifice</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">orifício de restrição</rdfs:label>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(RestrictionOrifice(x) ↔ FlowModificationAccessory(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowRestrictionFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f)))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every restriction orifice is a flow modification accessory that bears a flow restriction function</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um orifício de restrição é um acessório de modificação de fluxo que possui a função de restringir o fluxo de fluido criando queda de pressão controlada através de constrição geométrica.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A restriction orifice is a flow modification accessory that bears the function to restrict fluid flow by creating controlled pressure drop through geometric constriction.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b2720"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[ISO 15926-4] A &lt;RESTRICTION ORIFICE&gt; is a &lt;FLOW MODIFICATION ACCESSORY&gt; that is intended for use as a restrictor</skos:definition>
  </rdf:Description>
