  <rdf:Description rdf:about="https://www.inf.ufrgs.br/ontologies/copi/COPI_0000116">
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="pt-br">elemento de vazão</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">flow element</rdfs:label>
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class"/>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[CFIHOS] A detecting element that is producing a signal that is proportional to a flow rate.</skos:definition>
    <skos:definition xml:lang="en">[POSC Caesar] A device located in a flowstream measuring the flow.</skos:definition>
    <iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom xml:lang="en">∀x(FlowElement(x) ↔ (Instrument(x) ∧ ∃f(FlowMeasurementFunction(f) ∧ bearerOf(x,f))))</iof-av:firstOrderLogicAxiom>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="pt-br">Um elemento de vazão é um instrumento que tem a função de medir vazões em um fluxo e produzir sinais proporcionais à vazão medida.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition xml:lang="en">A flow element is an instrument that has the function to measure flow rates in a flowstream and produce signals proportional to the measured flow.</iof-av:naturalLanguageDefinition>
    <iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom xml:lang="en">Every flow element is an instrument that bears a FlowMeasurementFunction and has component parts including a FlowSensingElement and SignalGenerationComponent.</iof-av:semiFormalNaturalLanguageAxiom>
    <owl:equivalentClass rdf:nodeID="nc1a1cc74203240db84b8ecd910de6f90b1477"/>
  </rdf:Description>
